


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7ad2c18d:


    pl "I think I like you a little too much, Dr. Grette. Haha!"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_817b8c61:


    gr "I like you, too, [na2]!"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_93a2303c:


    gr "But knock it off with the jokes. {w}Give me a serious answer."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_fd347a41:


    nar "Jokes? That off-hand remark hits me like a gut punch. {w}Though I guess a statement like that would sound like a joke in this kind of situation."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_989670f3:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e36b0c0f:


    pl "Doc... You really won't tell anyone?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_cc8cf3b9:


    gr "Not a soul, I swear. Whatever you're worried about, your secret's safe with me, [na2]."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e78ce760:


    nar "I've only just broached the subject and already my hands are shaking. I never thought I'd tell anyone about the memories I've kept hidden away all this time."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_8755277e:


    nar "It would be one thing if I were confiding in another guy, but Dr. Grette is a woman."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_d82c7d41:


    nar "The moment I confide in her about what's bothering me, it'll go from a mere incident to a more serious problem."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e560aa21:


    nar "Not to mention, she's an unrelated third party. It's not that I don't trust her not to say anything, but she'll be the first person outside of the Cleanup Department who'll know about it."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b6cb3223:


    pl "This is something like my sixth day here, right?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_45e83ee5:


    gr "Yes... That's right. I remember well. {w}The day you arrived at the temple was also the first time we met."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b5deefe7:


    pl "I thought so... To tell you the truth, I've felt out of place in my department since the very beginning, probably because I'm not from around here and I was invited to transfer over to the Magic Department..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_98df61a6:


    gr "Neither of those reasons are valid excuses for ostracizing another human being."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b4c6ce51:


    pl "That's not the problem... Well, I mean, of course it sucks, but it doesn't really bother me all that much."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_dd0c9c05:


    pl "At any rate... There were two priests who talked with me on my first day here."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_709ede3e:


    gr "Okay."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_1af70346:


    pl "To be honest, I wouldn't say they were necessarily all that friendly, but there was so much I didn't know and they showed me around..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_43caef05:


    pl "One of them is close to Maya, and since I'm always with her, we've naturally grown beyond mere acquaintances. The other one, however..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a02fca8c:


    pl "Well... She was weirdly nice to me, but the first time I saw her, she struck me as kind of a bad apple, if you get my gist..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7296191c:


    pl "All I'm trying to say is she just rubbed me the wrong way... {w}Do you know what I'm trying to say?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_397f01ca:


    gr "Do you mean her mannerisms and way of speaking made you uncomfortable?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_ef68cfa0:


    pl "Right, right. {w}There are people like that everywhere. Folks who pull insensitive pranks without a basic understanding of when they've gone too far..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_44832c14:


    pl "When we first met, I was brand new to the temple and was completely clueless about basically everything. It would have been nice to have at least one person treat me kindly..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_85a5c237:


    pl "I decided I didn't want anything to do with her."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_223c23ef:


    gr "I see..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_ee6dc27d:


    nar "The preamble to my problem is growing excessively long. Get the point, dummy..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_5b82b06d:


    pl "At any rate, it had been a few days since then, right? {w}And she didn't show up for work. She said she wasn't feeling well, but according to her friend..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_deb7630a:


    pl "Uh, I'm talking about the other person I mentioned. The one who's friends with Maya? I don't think I mentioned she's a girl, huh?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_9fe1d29f:


    pl "So she's a girl. Actually, both of them are... I used to hate it when the guys would tease me for only ever having friends who were girls. {w}What was I talking about again?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_f20702a3:


    pl "Right. According to her friend, she usually says she isn't feeling well as an excuse to not work."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_aafaa534:


    gr "The two people who helped you out are both women, [na2]?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_216d8eae:


    nar "She murmurs the question under her breath, as if speaking to herself, as she jots something down--a note on a thick sheaf of paper that I can't see from where I'm sitting."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b3ef6f29:


    pl "You're taking notes?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_6ce9de55:


    gr "Of course."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7f7f9c7a:


    gr "Oh, right... My memory is pretty terrible, and I know it's not easy for you to open up, so I want to make sure I remember everything so your problem gets the attention it deserves."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_df4dad57:


    gr "Don't worry about it. Keep going."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_dbe8eac0:


    nar "I'm not completely satisfied with her explanation, but I've already come too far to stop now. {w}I swallow hard in an attempt at refocusing."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_4db0f0da:


    pl "It was the middle of the night and she was in her pajamas. She asked if I could bring her some water. {w}I really didn't want to, but..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_23db855c:


    pl "I felt like I couldn't say no either, so I went inside, and she closed the door behind me... Which is how we ended up in her room alone..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_709ede3e_1:


    gr "Okay."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_022a5065:


    pl "Wh-Which is when I... {w}I swear I didn't plan on doing anything when I agreed to get the water! It's just that she suddenly spilled her water on me, and the bed was right behind me..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_8c5a4940:


    pl "I didn't plan on doing anything like that, but I have a feeling she did. From the very beginning."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_436eea68:


    pl "That's right... Since the first time we met, she'd treated me kindly for the sole purpose of doing what she did. Honestly, I wish I'd noticed beforehand, but..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_bcc0cba2:


    pl "The thought never even crossed my mind, you know? I tried to tell her I wasn't interested, but I didn't seem to have any control over the situation..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_f8d0236d:


    nar "I'm beginning to hyperventilate, something I've never experienced before. Even my heart is beating erratically."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_2acf67eb:


    nar "If she had simply nodded along indifferently, I probably would have burst into tears right then and there."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7a146c4c:


    gr "That must have been a terrible thing to experience."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_ee4f1738:


    nar "It seems she missed part of my narrative, which is a shame, but the important thing is that she views me as the victim here."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e3d0b902:


    nar "I'm just glad she's hearing my side of the story as a neutral third party, meaning I don't have to worry about her connecting the dots between what I'm saying and the incident the other day."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_89bb3a44:


    pl "It was... Though I feel better after telling you what happened."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7a799ed8:


    gr "Yeah? I'm glad to hear that... {w}Do you have any related problems you want to talk about?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_22d8f06b:


    pl "Well..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_99774a7b:


    pl "Maybe... But only a little. Um... {w}Kind of, yeah. Though I can talk to you without any real problems."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_26b37488:


    gr "Right. Well, I'm glad you have some experience doing so."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_4a153d9c:


    nar "Though her expression doesn't change, she seems to be thinking rather seriously about something."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_48f512f8:


    nar "I'm not a huge fan of her tendency to abruptly stop talking mid-conversation, seemingly lost in thought."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_2368b311:


    nar "I have a strong feeling I said way too much about something I never needed to bring up."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_ee76a2fe:


    gr "Okay, I want you to try something."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c0d08af8:


    nar "She hands me her pen before ripping out three sheets of paper from her notebook and giving them to me."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_12ce32ef:


    gr "Draw me a tree, a house, and a person. {w}However you want."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_14889435:


    pl "Huh? But why?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_81aefc2a:


    gr "Because your doctor wants to see your drawing skills! {w}Don't think about it too hard. Just take your time and have fun!"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_4d8814c4:


    nar "Telling me not to think about it too hard only makes me do just that..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_971286a5:


    nar "I guess I have no choice but to do what she wants. I don't have much drawing experience, so hopefully whatever I come up with doesn't look too ridiculous."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_42a9c0f0:


    nar "After using my shabby artistic skills to draw the picture she requested, she takes back the three scraps of paper, looks at each intently, and then spreads them out in front of me."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7bd19134:


    gr "Is this round thing on the tree some kind of abrasion?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_76119e45:


    pl "Um... It's the ring that marks its age? Trees have that, right? Well, maybe it's more like a knot."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_612f5745:


    gr "So then an animal lives in there?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_16ef4379:


    pl "I don't think anything lives there."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_76b7815f:


    gr "Why's that? It's a beautiful tree."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_6f4d891f:


    pl "It looks that way from the outside, but it's rotting away on the inside."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_556e5335:


    nar "I see, she answers casually while scribbling more notes in her notepad that I can't see."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_275794aa:


    nar "Then she holds out another of my drawings."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_8ab7706b:


    gr "Is this a brick house?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b4d61992:


    pl "Well... It could be? I honestly didn't give it that much thought."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e885b757:


    gr "Oh, and the sun is laughing!"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_194c314a:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eb3b44f7:


    gr "Who lives in this house?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_1d4e188e:


    pl "I have no idea. I didn't think that far."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_30fe1823:


    gr "So think about it now. In your mind, can you see a man living here? Or a woman?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eceaa752:


    pl "Hmm... Probably a man."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_fb9a9463:


    gr "What kind of man?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a961e4b2:


    pl "A man who's... employed? He didn't want to live with his family, so... {w}He moved into his own house?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_4d0a7de9:


    gr "How's he doing right now?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_83a154ca:


    pl "Not that great... He likes talking to people, but other people don't seem to like him all that much."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_0eb35c10:


    gr "What keeps him up at night?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_54f2b8f3:


    pl "Hrm... His girlfriend. {w}Things aren't going well between them. Mainly because it's more of a situationship than an actual relationship."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_64353188:


    pl "He doesn't really want to date anyone, and he has no plans on getting married, and yet no one will leave him alone."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a34cdf5b:


    pl "Even his mom... She gave birth to him and then carelessly tossed him aside, and yet here he is doing the same exact thing, and it makes him sick."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_17d935e9:


    gr "Does he remind you of anyone?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_024abddf:


    nar "I shut my mouth."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_d234af96:


    nar "At that moment, I knew what she'd been trying to drag out of me. {w}It's not that I can't answer her question, but I simply don't want to."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_5374ba2d:


    nar "Questions she's asked me about my favorite things, my family, and my dreams float through my mind."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c80ca7d8:


    nar "She wants to talk about stuff that I'd prefer not having to think about. She thinks I need her to help me."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_81113cb3:


    nar "She's treating me like one of her patients."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_8d6d37d4:


    gr "[na2]..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_f28ee0d2:


    pl "Yes."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_86fc3262:


    gr "Good answer. {w}In that case, how about you listen to what I have to say with that same enthusiasm?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a74e0a0f:


    pl "I'm sorry?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b7fc406c:


    gr "Let's see, where should I start... I'm sure you're already well aware, but all the priests here in the temple take a basic vow of celibacy while here, which includes a ban on all contraceptives."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_6da710df:


    gr "Do you have an idea on why that might be?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_50ba112c:


    gr "Correct... It borders on bioethics, but in short, it's because abortion is a felony."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e91568e4:


    gr "When a sperm meets an egg, there's a possibility of fertilization."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b251e4a8:


    gr "Following fertilization, the egg divides into many different cells, which in turn develops into an embryo which will take the form of a baby that we're all familiar with."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_8d2e8685:


    gr "Which is why us priests view that egg as a human being from the moment it's fertilized."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_cec5d087:


    gr "The reason why birth control is forbidden in the temple is due to its inability to perfectly prevent all pregnancies. But also because it prevents the implantation of an embryo."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eb364c7d:


    gr "There are lots of people who find it difficult to trust the tools we have and modern medicine to be foolproof when it comes to prevention."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_8995139d:


    gr "If there's still even the slightest chance of pregnancy, then it's better to simply abstain altogether... {w}More or less."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_83219c7e:


    pl "What's your point?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_82c72e9e:


    gr "Sorry, you must be wondering why I started talking about that out of the blue, huh?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eb1e660c_3:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c7453d7d:


    gr "Because life, after all, is given to us from God himself,"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_d9430074:


    gr "and we are born with a desire to nurture new life within ourselves."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_76a7fd2d:


    gr "There are plenty of people in the world who give in to their desires and make mistakes from doing so, I strongly believe that every emotion we are capable of having is necessary."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_67620ff4:


    gr "And as proof, it's absolutely imperative we harbor lust for our fellow humans. {w}In order to survive as a race, we need to be able to create new life."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_cb28dc4c:


    gr "And that life we create in its own self is incredibly precious and pure."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eb1e660c_4:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c4031557:


    gr "Of course, what you went through was absolutely traumatizing, [na2], and I'm not negating your experience..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_55a25b49:


    gr "And until then, I'll help you find ways to distance those painful memories so you can take care of yourself."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a703499d:


    pl "Love?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c43e33e3:


    gr "Yes. Throughout our lives, we meet people, fall in love, and teach that child to love so they may repeat the cycle."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_f518f9dc:


    pl "So you've had relations with Bishop Greg?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_2f82ab07:


    gr "What?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_160635ea:


    nar "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_160635ea_1:


    nar "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_148f5b8f:


    gr "I know it seems like a lot right now, but I'll be with you every step of the way, no matter how long it takes."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_502b83b0:


    nar "There's the doctor side."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_eb1e660c_5:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7fe3f78e:


    pl "Doc... You're a doctor, right?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_ce48f1f7:


    gr "Yes?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_1aa84797:


    pl "You're a doctor, which is why you so easily assess my problems, define them as some kind of disorder that needs correcting, and then order me to do so under the guise of a request."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_6f4e539d:


    pl "You don't care about my future, long-term or otherwise. You thoughtlessly throw phrases like \"you can do it\" around so you can simply get through this singular moment."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_3b0da508:


    pl "You comfort yourself by saying everything you do is for the priests, which is how you curry favor, praise, and trust from the people around you,"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c503423f:


    pl "when all I really want is to be able to collect my thoughts without a need to find a solution right away."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_5a5b09c0:


    gr "[na2]...?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_44914db5:


    pl "Doc."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_f46883d8:


    nar "My cup falls to the ground, spilling the milk that was left inside all over the floor."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_30f8b8b8:


    nar "I slowly stand up and move to where she's sitting on the couch across from me."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_fb7a82cb:


    nar "She sits there, her eyes following my movement before suddenly getting to her feet, as if having sensed something's wrong. {w}I grab her arm."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_9576982f:


    nar "I press my leg against her knee, gradually increasing the pressure."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_84691cb0:


    nar "I notice a stigma on her slender wrist, trembling in my grip as she struggles to get free, just like on the first day I met her."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_37b9dd7b:


    gr "[na2]!" with sshake


translate English day6_gr_rkn_1b5a8d4a:


    pl "Yet I trust you, doc."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_2dfa8b1f:


    nar "Renewed strength suddenly surges into her arm."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_506bc58b:


    nar "Of the five fingers that sprout from her hand like roots from a tree, only her ring finger, the most delicate one, is adorned by a silver ring."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a155b383:


    nar "It makes me realize that, compared to me, she's an incredibly weak and slim woman. {w}I wish I had noticed much sooner."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a8f1805d:


    pl "Do you trust me?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_gr_rkn_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_gr_rkn_6a9312a2:


    "\n She flails around in an attempt at breaking free though she makes no move to shove or hit me, probably realizing in a battle of strength she doesn't stand a chance. It's not long before her frightened screams die down as well."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_65628727:


    et "Due to her position of trust, she is prohibited from harming a priest under her care and it'd be impossible for her to shove me away without using some degree of violence. She probably also realized what might happen to her if someone catches us like this."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7b6b7344:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"[na2], stop...!\" She murmurs one last, hoarse plea. {w}It holds no hint of resistance, instead coming off as a request. As if clinging to a shred of hope she can't let herself give up on. It strikes me as perfunctory instead of optimistic."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_f193748c:


    et "It doesn't matter, though, as I kiss her without listening to her request. I'm not her student, and I'm under no obligation to do anything she asks me to."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b87c6977:



    nvl clear
    "\n I need her to acknowledge the person I am. {w}I'm not some young kid she needs to dote on or a pathetic patient who needs to be cured. I need her to see me as an adult, a human being. {w}And that the feelings I hold for that man are not merely respect or compassion but vulgar jealousy."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_2cb254bb:


    et "I was happier when I didn't know. Perhaps my relationship with them would've remained unchanged if I'd remained ignorant to the truth. {w}But the good doctor herself taught me that every emotion we experience as humans is valid. So there must be a legitimate reason for this dark desire to exist inside me."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_gr_rkn_9c901178:


    "\n I force her closed mouth open and shove my tongue in.{w} As I lick her rigid teeth and unmoving tongue, her slender arms and legs tremble."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c231c93c:


    "Her mouth is surprisingly soft.{w} The more I move, the looser the boundaries that are her lips get, enough that I could just eat her up."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_91efd66b:


    et "As I feel her warm breath that has a lingering smell of sweet treats, I can also hear her crying, and it almost sounds like she's moaning."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_8985ca9d:



    nvl clear
    "\n The new feelings I harbor inside me are red hot, and yet instead of being warmed up by this vigorous exercise, she's bizarrely cold. She simply too thin to naturally generate enough heat."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b9913666:


    "The flesh that covers her slender bones is less firm compared to the muscles in my limbs, the skin on her plump arms and thighs jiggling with each movement."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_3cf25b52:


    et "What a rundown body. {w}And yet all I want is to hold her close to me."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c94e6e90:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"I guess the bishop must be too busy to stop by..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_af262295:


    et "Though if I were him, I'd never leave you alone, Dr. Grette.\""


translate English day6_gr_rkn_22e31480:



    nvl clear
    "\n She simply stares at me without speaking, her gaze vacant and unfocused. {w}My attempt at purposefully saying her name seems to have paid off."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_7cdb4b8d:


    et "In retrospect, I'd been terrified this whole time of looking directly into those clear eyes of hers. {w}She's always trying to make eye contact with me, and I find myself forced to face the truth behind why I consistently avoid doing so."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_90c2e9a4:



    nvl clear
    "\n I hate that I avoid her gaze without realizing I'm doing so. And yet a part of me feels as if all the misfortune and mistakes that I've brushed off as inconsequential would turn into grave sins in her eyes."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_38201a91:


    "And I would, in turn, become a sinner. So by avoiding her gaze, I can in turn avoid facing the truth, and there's nothing she can do aside from breathe, her dry lips twitching with each inhale and exhale."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_526f9f3d:


    et "To be honest, seeing her in this state doesn't make me happy, but I also understand I've come too far to go back now. Just like how she's accepted there's no use in struggling at this point."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a70cf8fe:



    nvl clear
    "\n I've almost forgotten why I adored her as an adult or saw her as any kind of support pillar."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_a8dfba56:


    et "I wonder if she ever actually behaved like an adult or if I simply misread her actions based on her age. Even now, her face is filthy with tears, like a child."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_76b2fe88_3:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_gr_rkn_c4f34948:


    nar "She's no longer moving."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e0b04555:


    nar "She's breathing, and it's clear that she's simply too exhausted and worn-out to lift even a finger,"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_bb9eb784:


    nar "and yet I'm afraid she'll get too cold in the airtight and insulated infirmary."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_61ecc095:


    nar "I look to my side and see her glass of milk on the table and an old camera."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_d60fc26e:


    nar "I find myself holding the camera once more. {w}It's not that heavy, and yet my hands tremble under its weight."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_d9a941af:


    nar "Peering through the lens, I see the doctor is no longer facing the camera."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_0d02a55a:


    nar "The camera spits out a damp piece of paper accompanied by the sound of a loud flash."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_5a1f7557:


    nar "The light from the camera causes the silver ring on her hand which dangles lifelessly over the edge of the couch to briefly glow a bright white."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_4d6d6209:


    pl "Doc. {w}I'll be going now."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_31eee243:


    nar "Before I leave, I give a final farewell to the body which no longer houses any part of the former doctor's soul."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_b0a9f8ae:


    nar "I walk out, staggering under my own weight."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_1885f789:


    nar "Mentally I'm exhausted, yet my body feels as light as a feather."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e9dc728f:


    nar "As I wander through the halls of the temple, my feet carry me along as if they have a mind of their own. {w}I watch as the scenery around me changes and people pass me by."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_abe2e83b:


    nar "I really fucked things up big time, somewhat literally. {w}I wonder what'll happen now?"


translate English day6_gr_rkn_54f068c4:


    nar "If word of what I've done gets out, everyone at the temple will start giving me second looks."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_160635ea_2:


    nar "..."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_89dca27b:



    nvl clear
    "\n When I raise my head, I see a light. A brilliantly bright light that urges me forward, the type that burns forever, unable to be extinguished."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_f29c5c12:


    "I wasn't wandering aimlessly after all. I'd returned to this spot on purpose."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e99f4a4d:


    et "Two big wings, so white they're almost blinding, clearly not of this world."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_9271b365:



    nvl clear
    "\n My vision darkens, my eyes unable to bear the light in all its brilliance. My head naturally falls forward, and I drop to my knees."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_6b214259:


    "I raise my trembling hands, reaching out to touch her skin. {w}A part of me is pained that I know no other way to show my respect to her."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_2f667f8b:


    "And yet the angel still grants a deplorable wretch like me a chance. She allows me to touch her. Uncontrollably, I start to cry."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_d0cb3ef7:


    "I gently cup her soft hands in mine and weep like a newborn baby."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_781dfd15:


    et "I'm touching an angel. And yet my eyes aren't gouged from their sockets, I'm able to speak without vomiting, and even my spirit is clear without the hint of a headache."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_69cca741:



    nvl clear
    "\n The angel manifested in this world for me. {w}Oh, god. Thank you, my beloved angel."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_361a1f97:


    "Please find a way to forgive me. {w}I beg for your mercy and benevolence."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_4b483f0d:


    et "Forgive me my sins."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_22dc0e43:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"I... I forced myself on Dr. Grette, the auxiliary bishop of the Health Department."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_f109e54f:


    "And even though she told me to stop, tried to shake me off, told me no... it didn't stop me from fulfilling my inexorable desire to sleep with her."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_53c229c5:


    "I insulted her humanity and even took a photo of her used shell of a body...\""


translate English day6_gr_rkn_bf7296b4:



    nvl clear
    "\n By admitting what I did out loud, I give my sin weight."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_6caee1bf:


    "And it's only after I give voice to every single thing I did that I'm able to come to grips with the reality of the situation."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_23e45339:


    "The bright light continues to wash over me, preventing me from hiding my sin or escaping from its repercussions. {w}Though as long as the angel forgives me, I can keep my humanity."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_e8240e71:


    et "Within the shadow cast by her wings, as the warm wind blows onto me... I welcome the most beautiful light in all the world."


translate English day6_gr_rkn_76b2fe88_4:


    nvl clear


translate English day7_gr_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day7_gr_8804abba:



    nvl clear
    "\n I had a very, very long dream. With my vision blurred and my head throbbing in pain as if trapped in a vice, it feels like I've been asleep for seven days."


translate English day7_gr_c633cf33:


    "All I know for sure is that my consciousness remains trapped in that dream, though I can't for the life of me remember what happened."


translate English day7_gr_7a26e823:


    "I get the feeling I had a nightmare, but I also feel like it wasn't so bad, too."


translate English day7_gr_94aca8d8:


    "With long dreams, they're usually so pleasant that you never want to wake up--or so terrifying that it's impossible to come back to the waking world."


translate English day7_gr_648c3dd7:


    "Not wanting to think about it any more, I sink my throbbing head into my pillow. {w}I'm so done with thinking."


translate English day7_gr_d7ae7cd2:


    "How much time have I wasted on dreaming lately?"


translate English day7_gr_c4056ed6:


    et "At least there's no need for that any more. {w}Because my angel talks to me when I'm awake, too."


translate English day7_gr_478b31fc:



    nvl clear
    "\n With my head facing the wall, I find myself observing the brilliant, white light shining in through the window."


translate English day7_gr_8105756b:


    "The sun which had set the night before has once again risen in all its luminous glory. {w}It's morning, I think absently to myself, taking the sight of that faint, brilliant light for granted."


translate English day7_gr_91031fe1:


    "My body feels sluggish. {w}My head pulses painfully even with my eyes shut tight, but there's no way I'm falling back to sleep."


translate English day7_gr_9cc593e7:


    "Is there a chance that it's not my imagination? Maybe I've really been asleep for a week. A part of me hopes that's true, though I know it's simply not possible."


translate English day7_gr_3923c360:


    et "As my mind slowly wakes up, memories of yesterday wash over me in vivid detail. I try to make a mental checklist of everything I need to do today."


translate English day7_gr_06a49c8f:



    nvl clear
    "\n First of all, I have to get up. {w}I should try and get to the bathroom to wash up ahead of the morning rush. And while I'm at it, I should tackle the pile of dirty laundry that's built up."


translate English day7_gr_108d26cd:


    et "Then, once I'm tidied up and ready for the day ahead, I'll say good morning to Maya before participating in the bishop's morning lesson. {w}It's still kind of awkward seeing her, but there shouldn't be any problems simply listening to her lecture."


translate English day7_gr_f0780563:



    nvl clear
    "\n Work's hard, but I'll manage like I always do. {w}I'm still pretty new, but I'm slowly getting used to things."


translate English day7_gr_b456ec53:


    "Here I am, staring up at my familiar ceiling, wrapped in my blanket that reeks of sweat. {w}I can hear the footsteps of priests from the hallway getting ready for the day ahead."


translate English day7_gr_33fa2f05:


    "I can do all those things, but I don't want to. {w}And that's not just my work in the Cleanup Department, but anything at all, including getting out of bed."


translate English day7_gr_58c1b5f6:


    et "Call it simply laziness or me just not being in the mood. {w}Either way, I fold my hands over my stomach and decide to try falling asleep again."


translate English day7_gr_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day7_gr_a5731ac0:


    et "\n \"I'm your doctor, [na2]. {w}I can't help you if you don't open up to me about what's bothering you.\""


translate English day7_gr_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day7_gr_7be71fc5:



    nvl clear
    "\n I must have been laying there, resting my eyes, for about ten minutes."


translate English day7_gr_c96b4327:


    et "I struggle to heave my heavy body up. It's not because of the silence in the hallway causing anxiety, but because I know I should."


translate English day7_gr_76b2fe88_3:


    nvl clear


translate English day7_gr_52451a50:


    nar "A damp wind blows past my eyes, which are rough and dry at the moment.{w} I look again to see the sky is awfully cloudy."


translate English day7_gr_a2a27202:


    nar "Before entering the room, I stop myself for a moment.{w} About ten people come out of the room at once. Roll call must be over."


translate English day7_gr_72cd9e40:


    pl "Maya!"


translate English day7_gr_c45a297c:


    nar "I spot a familiar face from within the crowd and happily walk over to her."


translate English day7_gr_94be9f51:


    nar "The other priests shoot us curious glances as they file out into the hallway, observing the two of us walking side-by-side."


translate English day7_gr_771f900e:


    my "G-Good morning, [na2]."


translate English day7_gr_ada8473e:


    pl "Are you on your way to work?"


translate English day7_gr_02ed3da9:


    my "Y-Yeah. I, uh..."


translate English day7_gr_ea66451c:


    nar "As she shuffles along slowly, trying to get out of line, someone shoves her as they pass by." with sshake


translate English day7_gr_23ad2307:


    my "I'm on my way to work..."


translate English day7_gr_d011aff4:


    pl "What a piece of shit... He should have apologized."


translate English day7_gr_fe15b64e:


    my "..."


translate English day7_gr_1325bd30:


    pl "Are you okay?"


translate English day7_gr_e96ef804:


    my "I'm fine..."


translate English day7_gr_b6a16de3:


    pl "You don't have to act tough, Maya."


translate English day7_gr_3f8a468c:


    my "I'm not acting tough. {w}The hallway's narrow, and I was in their way... So, actually... it was my fault."


translate English day7_gr_0a2766f4:


    pl "Regardless what the situation might be, there's no possible excuse for hurting you, Maya."


translate English day7_gr_191e3960:


    my "He just ran into me, that's all. {w}B-But I appreciate your concern."


translate English day7_gr_a58871f5:


    pl "Maya... You really are kind-hearted. And you take your work seriously."


translate English day7_gr_307a2cab:


    my "Of course I do..."


translate English day7_gr_1f264497:


    pl "Let me help you with your work."


translate English day7_gr_042dc5c1:


    my "Huh?! {w}It's f-fine. I can handle it."


translate English day7_gr_b5b25e9f:


    pl "Why?"


translate English day7_gr_d4575b68:


    my "It's just... both of you have been helping me since I arrived, and so I thought I should really start trying to do it... on my own..."


translate English day7_gr_e7743325:


    pl "You don't need to work hard. And you don't need to make your own decisions. {w}Why not just live the rest of your life in comfort while letting other people help you?"


translate English day7_gr_ee214004:


    my "I... I have to go..."


translate English day7_gr_881772a4:


    nar "I watch her petite back slip further away from me as she runs down the hall. {w}I notice the unmistakable mark of the angel on it."


translate English day7_gr_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day7_gr_a65595e8:


    nar "As I stand in the now empty hallway, it's not long before I hear the raucous sound of guys' laughter coming from inside the office."


translate English day7_gr_ac8bbbbf:


    nar "Don't tell anyone."


translate English day7_gr_e0c24f37:


    nar "Those words play through my mind. Words spoken by the angel. {w}She doesn't want mere mortals to know of her existence."


translate English day7_gr_8936671a:


    nar "Only I can know. Because she chose me alone out of everyone."


translate English day7_gr_e4d0cc97:


    pl "Don't tell anyone..."


translate English day7_gr_b2ee2133:


    nar "I murmur her command, repeating it once more. My voice seems to solidify those formerly soundless words, giving them shape."


translate English day7_gr_a164a5b2:


    nar "I thought it might be closed, but the infirmary seems to be open like always."


translate English day7_gr_0bcdb311:


    nar "As soon as I open the door, motes of dust sparkling like tiny threads in the light catch my eye, and my entire body is enveloped in a mantle of heat."


translate English day7_gr_5ee0e252:


    nar "The infirmary is generally kept at a fairly warm temperature in order to welcome sick patients or exhausted priests,"


translate English day7_gr_bd3e7e16:


    nar "but the room feels hotter than usual today, perhaps due to the unusually direct sunlight."


translate English day7_gr_16911392:


    gr "Welcome."


translate English day7_gr_91bc5e15:


    nar "The moment I open the door, the doctor gets up out of her chair with a loud clatter. {w}I notice her attention focused on my feet for a split second."


translate English day7_gr_8e641cb4:


    nar "Then her gaze shifts to my face and her eyes crinkle as she smiles at me warmly."


translate English day7_gr_5a74d731:


    pl "Hey, doc. Not too busy today?"


translate English day7_gr_20fcec69:


    gr "Nope... Just taking it easy. {w}Though I'm still getting my paperwork done and doing some writing, of course."


translate English day7_gr_eda5b316:


    gr "But part of my job includes greeting priests at the infirmary."


translate English day7_gr_670300ed:


    pl "I wish you'd greet me not just because you're duty bound to."


translate English day7_gr_f6fb8cac:


    gr "I didn't mean for it to come out that way. You know you're always welcome here."


translate English day7_gr_bee5ba91:


    nar "She picks up a chair from her empty desk and puts it down across from her own."


translate English day7_gr_b25c7a93:


    nar "The backless chair seems light enough that she can easily set it down with one hand."


translate English day7_gr_8387d9c6:


    nar "The sound of steel, something I never thought I'd hear in the infirmary, somehow seems louder than it does in the workplace."


translate English day7_gr_10d5a68e:


    gr "I'm sorry, but I don't have any snacks for you today... {w}Want to take a seat and talk to me anyways?"


translate English day7_gr_5709a536:


    pl "The other priests ate all the snacks again, didn't they?"


translate English day7_gr_e0db6cae:


    gr "No... I usually get up early in order to bake snacks for the day, but I didn't have time this morning."


translate English day7_gr_af4bd8ec:


    pl "Ha ha! I guess even people like you sleep in sometimes, huh?"


translate English day7_gr_c697c5c4:


    gr "I wasn't feeling well..."


translate English day7_gr_29512d51:


    nar "She blinks her eyes sleepily, as if still drowsy. She really does look exhausted."


translate English day7_gr_df413a8c:


    gr "How have you been doing lately, [na2]?"


translate English day7_gr_fa6f74a2:


    pl "What do you mean?"


translate English day7_gr_361c64a5:


    gr "How's the pain in your healed arm, for example? Or any developments with the trouble you've been dealing with in the Cleanup Department? You've mentioned this stuff before,"


translate English day7_gr_b9fbf84a:


    gr "so I figured I'd ask just in case. Perhaps you've seen or heard something strange?"


translate English day7_gr_7c5221fd:


    pl "Right... Nothing really to talk about."


translate English day7_gr_b6c32c31:


    gr "That's good then. I worry about you, that's all."


translate English day7_gr_ef200cc6:


    pl "Honestly, I'm more worried about you... Are you sure you didn't catch a cold?"


translate English day7_gr_40dd9d66:


    gr "I didn't. I'm just a little tired. Work's been pretty busy lately. {w}You're really worried about me?"


translate English day7_gr_07e03e59:


    pl "I mean, the infirmary's way hotter than it usually is..."


translate English day7_gr_3b572105:


    pl "That, coupled with the fact that you don't seem in great shape, makes me worry that I'm somehow to blame for this."


translate English day7_gr_e07e6ab7:


    gr "You might be a little too sensitive, [na2]. Everything's the same as it always is."


translate English day7_gr_d5d8f0c3:


    gr "Well, aside from the fact that I didn't get to bake any sweets today..."


translate English day7_gr_f5942ea0:


    gr "Heh! Do you tend to run hot, [na2]?"


translate English day7_gr_968154e6:


    pl "I think it's more like you run cold, Doc."


translate English day7_gr_6fdf95cd:


    gr "You're probably right..."


translate English day7_gr_b2ea2b8f:


    nar "A shadow passes over her face, as if further proof of how exhausted she is. {w}Or maybe it's a vague recollection of yesterday's events."


translate English day7_gr_d9c37da2:


    nar "Does she think I don't remember what happened?"


translate English day7_gr_d540b906:


    nar "If I simply refuse to bring it up, will she act like it never happened?"


translate English day7_gr_b9ce050b:


    gr "[na2], do you, by chance, happen to keep a written journal?"


translate English day7_gr_a1e5fede:


    pl "A journal?"


translate English day7_gr_984a6c3e:


    gr "A brief summary of your thoughts or remarkable things you did during the day that you write down before you go to bed at night."


translate English day7_gr_05f9c2b2:


    pl "No. I've never done anything like that. Why do you ask?"


translate English day7_gr_e52baff2:


    gr "I told you the other day that I was going to help you, didn't I, [na2]?"


translate English day7_gr_b2efa2ec:


    gr "But I actually have no idea what you do during the day or what kind of things you think about."


translate English day7_gr_a33f5de3:


    gr "You are pretty open with me, but I'm sure even you have things you find difficult to tell me directly."


translate English day7_gr_5d99e7a7:


    gr "I can tell just by looking at you that you're someone who thinks about things a lot..."


translate English day7_gr_0ce9a939:


    pl "Can't I just be with you all day?"


translate English day7_gr_80e3da5c:


    gr "Hahaha... I wouldn't have anything to worry about if that were the case, but as humans, we can't just stay with one person forever."


translate English day7_gr_de50e0ab:


    gr "Our hearts grow stronger by interacting with all different kinds of people."


translate English day7_gr_a4a21e0f:


    pl "But aren't there people out there who only end up breaking our hearts?"


translate English day7_gr_986a92b6:


    gr "And there's also people who help our hearts to heal."


translate English day7_gr_cc7152d0:


    gr "They say painful experiences can oftentimes break someone, but there are other times when they act as a foundation to help us grow stronger."


translate English day7_gr_52f4e377:


    pl "Even more so when it's repeated countless times I guess, right?"


translate English day7_gr_96baa46f:


    gr "Have you experienced something similar while working in the Cleanup Department, [na2]?"


translate English day7_gr_4d4847ac:


    pl "You mean related to people dying and stuff?"


translate English day7_gr_1748761f:


    gr "Correct..."


translate English day7_gr_a6637edf:


    pl "I'm not sure. {w}It's like you said... At first, I couldn't even look at a corpse without getting freaked out, but after a while, I got used to it."


translate English day7_gr_048a7c14:


    pl "The grief of the bereaved and the rotten stench that permeates the Cleanup Department itself... None of it fazes me now. {w}But is it really okay to get used to something like looking death in the face?"


translate English day7_gr_6fcbc760:


    pl "I have no intention of doing this job for the rest of my life. Rather, I don't feel strong when I see these gory scenes and feel nothing."


translate English day7_gr_d2b7fcf1:


    pl "It comes off as simply a form of ethical compartmentalization."


translate English day7_gr_b2bbea9b:


    gr "There's a difference between getting numb to something and losing one's sense of morality, which is why you have to hang in there and talk to other people about how you feel."


translate English day7_gr_45b55251:


    gr "I've seen numerous patients while employed here and sent countless dead bodies to the morgue, and it pains me every time..."


translate English day7_gr_509863a4:


    gr "And yet I'm still here, refusing to let what I deal with break me."


translate English day7_gr_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "..."


translate English day7_gr_f7739dbb:


    gr "Look... If what you're dealing with is some kind of survivor's guilt, then you need to work on getting used to it. {w}What exactly do you mean?"


translate English day7_gr_ff996b14:


    pl "Do you hate me, Doc?"


translate English day7_gr_c0d8854f:


    gr "Of course not! There's no way I could hate you, [na2]!"


translate English day7_gr_b2de50cb:


    pl "It's just that you're acting slightly different than usual. {w}You don't trust me, huh? The way you're talking makes it sound like..."


translate English day7_gr_e9a57385:


    pl "Everything that's happened to me isn't a big deal and I'm blowing things out of proportion."


translate English day7_gr_67ad9793:


    gr "[na2]..."


translate English day7_gr_3e1964b3:


    nar "She sighs before grasping my hand in hers. They're smaller than mine, but her skin is smooth and cold to the touch."


translate English day7_gr_388adf56:


    gr "I'm sorry. It seems I made you worry by overthinking this. {w}I shouldn't have done that... I'm embarrassed for having you see me in such an immature light."


translate English day7_gr_2347d9ee:


    gr "I've never once made light of the pain you carry. And if you're suffering because of it... {w}Well then, that's a big problem."


translate English day7_gr_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "..."


translate English day7_gr_3520007b:


    gr "I'm not a perfect person, and there's a chance I still don't fully grasp the extent of your problems, [na2]."


translate English day7_gr_9059730e:


    gr "But I'm interested in learning more."


translate English day7_gr_4a9230e1:


    gr "And I want to help you. So I'm hoping you could tell me a little more about what's going on... {w}Okay?"


translate English day7_gr_f37a7a26:


    nar "I understand what she means when she talks about being strong. {w}She definitely is an example of such."


translate English day7_gr_14d019e0:


    nar "She stands strong despite everything she's been through, wanting nothing more than to protect me as my doctor. She's still able to look me straight in the eyes without turning away."


translate English day7_gr_73a5a043:


    nar "I get the feeling, based on what she said, that this type of thing has happened to her several times before during her employment here as a therapist."


translate English day7_gr_fcfc2969:


    nar "Which only means I'm nothing special."


translate English day7_gr_4cb9c894:


    nar "At the end of the day, I'm nothing more than one of her patients, just like the rest..."


translate English day7_gr_75f281ca:


    pl "Do you like spending time with me? {w}Or do you just want to help me?"


translate English day7_gr_e8e9624a:


    gr "In your opinion, [na2], is there a difference between those two thoughts?"


translate English day7_gr_99d02606:


    pl "I don't know... Actually, it's not that I don't know, but more like I really don't want to explain the way I see it."


translate English day7_gr_41ec7596:


    pl "Besides, if you had to pick, you'd probably choose the option you'd think I'd want you to say, right?"


translate English day7_gr_ae2df24d:


    gr "I just want to chat with you more, [na2], and help you find a way to live an easier life."


translate English day7_gr_9532b017:


    gr "I can tell there are still plenty of things that weigh on your mind, [na2], and you want to talk to me about them, but you can't."


translate English day7_gr_4013291c:


    gr "When these intrusive thoughts eventually explode, how does it make you feel? {w}It must weigh on you almost stiflingly so, right?"


translate English day7_gr_a9f812a2:


    pl "I don't remember everything in detail, but... {w}Actually, now I'm kind of mad. Which is why, earlier. Just a little."


translate English day7_gr_dc6eca7b:


    gr "Yes, let's work with that. I want you to write down the first three thoughts that come to mind."


translate English day7_gr_089c184d:


    pl "What's the point?"


translate English day7_gr_afc4282e:


    gr "The thing about thoughts is they're surprisingly easy to deal with simply by telling them to someone else."


translate English day7_gr_ac05586b:


    gr "Even when I think I have it all neatly organized in my head, I discover what a mess it truly is when I try to actually verbalize it aloud or write it down."


translate English day7_gr_05a9c947:


    gr "But more importantly, you like talking to people, don't you, [na2]?"


translate English day7_gr_8a08639c:


    pl "I guess..."


translate English day7_gr_138eee62:


    gr "I'm sure there have been times when you use conversations as sounding boards to organize your thoughts?"


translate English day7_gr_7abc6551:


    pl "Yeah... But I still don't understand what your point is. What are you getting at?"


translate English day7_gr_d34f0a76:


    gr "This is partly because I'd like to know more about you, [na2], but more than that,"


translate English day7_gr_ae07826b:


    gr "I want to offer you a chance at introspection so you can organize the thoughts in your head."


translate English day7_gr_339fceaf:


    gr "Getting your thoughts in order might not seem like much, but the act itself is actually incredibly important."


translate English day7_gr_0d8fd2b2:


    pl "Just because you've sorted everything out doesn't make those problems go away, though, right?"


translate English day7_gr_91039500:


    gr "You're right in that it won't solve the problem directly, but it'll help in making a path toward the solution."


translate English day7_gr_1107f09b:


    gr "Why is this hard for you? Why did it happen? What's your most ideal outcome from the current situation?"


translate English day7_gr_c25a861d:


    gr "Or conversely, what bothers you the most about what happened? {w}We use the answers to these questions to figure out an appropriate solution to what bothers us."


translate English day7_gr_47b96eba:


    pl "Nothing's really coming to mind..."


translate English day7_gr_c6431d00:


    gr "Which in itself is evidence that you're having trouble collecting your thoughts in an orderly fashion."


translate English day7_gr_6e771ade:


    pl "Who are you to make that call?"


translate English day7_gr_466ea407:


    gr "I'm not, but... This is why I keep saying that you need space and time to reflect on what happened and how it makes you feel."


translate English day7_gr_814283e1:


    nar "The doc's grip is pretty weak."


translate English day7_gr_438ba1c1:


    nar "I move my hand as I try to feel her long fingers and every bump and ridge on her smooth nails."


translate English day7_gr_a58401c2:


    pl "Your ring's gone..."


translate English day7_gr_822a85b4:


    nar "It doesn't escape my notice when she seems to involuntarily pull back upon hearing my observation when she'd been holding mine until now without any sign of struggle."


translate English day7_gr_9515cc35:


    gr "I was so tired this morning I forgot to put it on, that's all. It's not a big deal."


translate English day7_gr_9e156e59:


    pl "No, it is a big deal. Why did you end up sleeping in to begin with?"


translate English day7_gr_2d331c48:


    gr "I was just exhausted, that's all..."


translate English day7_gr_bb29e396:


    pl "Why were you so exhausted?"


translate English day7_gr_4dba65ea:


    gr "..."


translate English day7_gr_b04f3120:


    pl "Was it because of me?"


translate English day7_gr_c7e2a26f:


    gr "For crying out loud. Nothing gets past you, huh? I surrender."


translate English day7_gr_3950877d:


    gr "I promise I'll be back to my usual solid and dependable self by tomorrow, so stop worrying about me so much, okay?"


translate English day7_gr_be24927d:


    pl "Have you been having nightmares? What are they about?"


translate English day7_gr_cc528491:


    nar "She lets go of my hand."


translate English day7_gr_44b6b4ff:


    nar "By the time the thought that I should grab her hand before she can break free flashes through my mind, it's too late. It slips free almost too easily."


translate English day7_gr_2d8cb0a5:


    gr "I don't really want to think about it. {w}Well... More like, I don't really remember anything specific. Most people don't remember their dreams, you know."


translate English day7_gr_e95b2d27:


    pl "So you're saying it's abnormal to remember them? I remember mine, every day in fact."


translate English day7_gr_8ce9dd18:


    gr "It's not abnormal. {w}But you're definitely an outlier when it comes to that."


translate English day7_gr_ebc9eedb:


    gr "The average person is so focused on their life outside of their dreams that it's impossible for them to remember what they envision while asleep."


translate English day7_gr_c2d0f842:


    pl "So you're saying my unconsciousness decided my dreams are more important than reality?"


translate English day7_gr_832b0eb9:


    gr "Not exactly... More like your brain works harder than most. {w}You said you dream every night? What kind of dreams?"


translate English day7_gr_d7fac45a:


    pl "I forget..."


translate English day7_gr_025a040f:


    gr "By that do you mean... You don't want to tell me? Or is that you actually don't remember?"


translate English day7_gr_586e7433:


    pl "Neither. It's better if I can forget them, so I'd prefer not talking about them."


translate English day7_gr_db7c6f6e:


    gr "Do they scare you?"


translate English day7_gr_991610dc:


    pl "No. {w}Actually, the opposite? Though I'm not sure why I feel that way."


translate English day7_gr_9b738400:


    gr "So it's not that you don't remember, it's that you don't want to remember, is that right?"


translate English day7_gr_a7e637ce:


    pl "No. I don't remember because I have to forget."


translate English day7_gr_90f10df2:


    pl "As someone who didn't want to talk about their dream, either, I'd assume you, of all people, would be able to understand that."


translate English day7_gr_b572e846:


    gr "Right, I'm sorry... {w}In that case, can I ask one last question? Did you make the decision to forget yourself?"


translate English day7_gr_18cd1970:


    gr "Or did someone else make it for you?"


translate English day7_gr_989670f3:


    pl "..."


translate English day7_gr_9c712fa3:


    gr "You don't have to answer if you don't want to, [na2]. {w}I'm assuming by forcing yourself to forget, you're doing so in the hopes of never having that dream again, hrm?"


translate English day7_gr_faefad90:


    pl "You said that was the last question."


translate English day7_gr_5b4e4eb7:


    gr "That one was more directed at myself. I have a lot of thoughts as well, and it helps me to say them out loud or write them down so I can organize them better..."


translate English day7_gr_9f878140:


    nar "She's once again holding her pen in her hand, which she hasn't touched all day. {w}She pauses between sentences, her eyes flicking over at me as if searching for something."


translate English day7_gr_65d68eda:


    nar "If my memory is correct, the doc is researching something. Unrelated to Pestis. {w}Something that can be cured by human hands..."


translate English day7_gr_d8fc469c:


    pl "I'm not sick, Doc."


translate English day7_gr_ab53bf49:


    nar "Her pen stops for a moment at the sound of that statement. She glances off to the side, looking at nothing in particular, before shifting her gaze back to me."


translate English day7_gr_efe727b6:


    gr "I know that. Though what defines any particular illness is up to the doctor to decide, not the individual."


translate English day7_gr_25ec5e1e:


    pl "So you're poking and prodding at me in order to collect some kind of ridiculous evidence?"


translate English day7_gr_3691035e:


    pl "You want me to be crazy, don't you? Because that would be in your best interests."


translate English day7_gr_3bd3d498:


    gr "Of course not."


translate English day7_gr_3fd42ffc:


    gr "It's not that I don't believe what you're telling me, [na2], but if you are sick, then I want to help you get better."


translate English day7_gr_2283fa4b:


    pl "It sounds like you don't believe me at all. So after you treat me like a psycho and fix me up, what then?"


translate English day7_gr_86dda209:


    pl "Gonna write up some kinda dissertation on mental illness? {w}You're just using me, aren't you?"


translate English day7_gr_a496211b:


    gr "Stop! That's enough! You're letting your emotions run away from you, [na2]! {w}Calm down! Or at the very least, take a seat!"


translate English day7_gr_eb1e660c_3:


    pl "..."


translate English day7_gr_2474a498:


    nar "I feel the urge to kick the stupid chair instead, to send it flying. But I know if I did that, she'd only grow more suspicious of me than she already is."


translate English day7_gr_98e18d2f:


    nar "I'm not a freaking psycho. {w}If I really were sick, my thoughts wouldn't be this rational and I wouldn't have been able to control my own impulsive rage."


translate English day7_gr_ab05dac1:


    nar "She picks up the pen she dropped and places it on her desk."


translate English day7_gr_a68f1323:


    nar "With her gaze focused directly on me instead of glancing over her paperwork, I notice a distance between us that I've never picked up on before."


translate English day7_gr_b150e322:


    gr "I have to say something, [na2], but I don't want you to take it the wrong way..."


translate English day7_gr_ffd76f92:


    gr "Everyone gets sick at some point in their lives, and all illnesses can be cured."


translate English day7_gr_949bdc3b:


    pl "And yet I'm not sick. There's all kinds of psychos in the world, people who do really fucked up things..."


translate English day7_gr_81634650:


    pl "No matter how many subcategories for crazy you might have, Doc, to the average person, all of them look exactly the same."


translate English day7_gr_954241be:


    gr "You're probably rejecting the very notion that you might be sick... {w}I understand completely."


translate English day7_gr_8b0e5683:


    gr "But that doesn't give you a pass to simply ignore your blatant symptoms. If you don't do something about it, you'll only get worse."


translate English day7_gr_9228e86b:


    pl "But I don't have auditory or visual hallucinations anymore, and my nightmares are gone."


translate English day7_gr_6a731a28:


    gr "I'm glad to hear that, but it doesn't mean you're all better. {w}Mere depression, stress, even delusional thinking are still all classified as mental illnesses."


translate English day7_gr_b7ce94ff:


    pl "Delusions are a mental illness?"


translate English day7_gr_54af43fd:


    gr "It's a symptom that can lead to such, yes."


translate English day7_gr_eae46231:


    gr "Delusions of grandeur, or on the opposite side of the spectrum, harboring an inferiority complex where you start to doubt your own existence,"


translate English day7_gr_88512f23:


    gr "paranoid behavior fueled by whispered commands that originate from your own unconscious mind... {w}I would say all of those things fall under the same schizophrenic umbrella."


translate English day7_gr_eb1e660c_4:


    pl "..."


translate English day7_gr_a8458bae:


    gr "There is one thing that ties all those seemingly varied symptoms together, and that is the pretext, the origin of the illness."


translate English day7_gr_f5638049:


    gr "And that is something harming you in some way. {w}That's usually the source most of the time."


translate English day7_gr_e98b1395:


    pl "I'm done."


translate English day7_gr_8d50c5a6:


    gr "Wait. That person you mentioned seeing in your dreams every night..."


translate English day7_gr_148c39f7:


    gr "Have you ever interacted with them while you're awake?"


translate English day7_gr_f94c20c7:


    pl "Stop. I said I don't want to hear anymore! Don't try to force anything more out of me!" with sshake


translate English day7_gr_07bab4fa:


    nar "And with a loud bang, the chair she'd brought over just for me ends up on its side on the ground."


translate English day7_gr_01d258a4:


    nar "I simply stand there, looking down at Dr. Grette who's still sitting in her seat."


translate English day7_gr_19c080be:


    nar "She furrows her brows in response to my sudden and very loud outburst, but the expression is quickly replaced by one of pity as she watches me."


translate English day7_gr_66c265de:


    gr "[na2], I..."


translate English day7_gr_05fbd9b4:


    pl "Shut up..."


translate English day7_gr_48dbbddb:


    gr "Fine... Let's end our conversation there for today."


translate English day7_gr_eb1e660c_5:


    pl "..."


translate English day7_gr_f488bdba:


    gr "I hope you'll take what I said to heart, [na2], and keep it in mind... {w}Feel free to stop by again tomorrow."


translate English day7_gr_3bbb4996:


    nar "Silence pervades the infirmary following that final statement. I stand there for a moment in the peaceful quiet, my breathing anxious and unsteady."


translate English day7_gr_c494f771:


    nar "Lukewarm cold sweat drips down from beneath my shirt collar, probably due to how hot it is in here. {w}Once my head cools down somewhat, I slowly turn around and begin making my way out, one sluggish step at a time."


translate English day7_gr_2a8b6e12:


    nar "I feel like I should give her some sort of goodbye, and yet I can't bring myself to say anything. {w}The room is so quiet."


translate English day7_gr_4da2f7a5:


    nar "I walk with my head down through the hall that's still bathed in a bright light. {w}I watch as my left and right foot repeatedly overtakes the other."


translate English day7_gr_2ab315ab:



    nvl clear
    "{nw}" with sshake


translate English day7_gr_d7c7ef3d:


    pl "Uh... What the hell?"


translate English day7_gr_26a6c2fe:


    nar "The moment I look up at the faint uncomfortable touch of someone tugging on my sleeve, I freeze."


translate English day7_gr_d7ad6c5a:


    gg "Heading back?"


translate English day7_gr_eb1e660c_6:


    pl "..."


