translate English day8_gr_21479440:


    gr "You'll catch a cold. {w}Go ahead and take a seat. I'll be right with you..."


translate English day8_gr_4dba65ea:


    gr "..."


translate English day8_gr_4eb95f12:


    nar "I used to think people's wrists were cold, but it's actually the opposite."


translate English day8_gr_53070c19:


    nar "The temperature of blood flowing through blue veins plainly visible underneath thin skin is hot."


translate English day8_gr_23982954:


    nar "Stigmata is the source of divine power, and hers is concentrated right here, in this spot. {w}She gathers her strength in her arm, pulling me closer."


translate English day8_gr_be509e4a:


    nar "I gently let go of her hand. {w}And yet I can still feel her pulse beating in my palm."


translate English day8_gr_68916de0:


    gr "Let me get something to clean you up with."


translate English day8_gr_8f7defad:


    nar "My soaking wet body shivers in the warm air of the infirmary. My hair weighs heavily against my scalp, to the point where I can't lift my head."


translate English day8_gr_5c04bce1:


    nar "Pale, red blood mixed with rain water drips onto the floor, staining the boards. {w}It's not long before a dry, rumpled towel is placed over my head."


translate English day8_gr_d6697cbb:


    nar "The emaciated branches swaying violently outside the window look like the blackened fingers of corpses, moving erratically in an almost beckoning gesture."


translate English day8_gr_4e56e29d:


    nar "It's not long before the towel becomes saturated with rainwater and red blood."


translate English day8_gr_a8633912:


    gr "I can get you some hot tea. Would you like some?"


translate English day8_gr_cd4499bf:


    nar "I slowly shake my head. {w}She seems more talkative than usual, in direct contrast to how quiet I am."


translate English day8_gr_39fb8db2:


    nar "I have a feeling, imagined or otherwise, that she's fully aware of what she's doing."


translate English day8_gr_18699b8b:


    gr "I'm sorry... We're all out of milk, so all I can offer you is tea. {w}You don't have to drink it, but it might help warm your hands up."


translate English day8_gr_432e9728:


    nar "There's that smell again. The smell of aromatic tea leaves burning... {w}She must have been brewing it for someone other than myself."


translate English day8_gr_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "..."


translate English day8_gr_17fe51e9:


    gr "Is something wrong?"


translate English day8_gr_eb1e660c_3:


    pl "..."


translate English day8_gr_e45fc548:


    gr "Work must have been rough considering the rain. {w}That's one downside to the capital. It rains even when it's sunny."


translate English day8_gr_eb1e660c_4:


    pl "..."


translate English day8_gr_90c63759:


    gr "You said you're sensitive to the cold, right? To tell you the truth, I'm pretty cold-blooded myself. In fact, I found myself conflicted this morning over whether to bring out my heavy-duty blanket or not."


translate English day8_gr_aa5182b7:


    pl "I'm sorry, Doc."


translate English day8_gr_2f82ab07:


    gr "Huh?"


translate English day8_gr_437b5a8c:


    pl "I didn't write anything in my journal."


translate English day8_gr_de895e20:


    gr "[na2]..."


translate English day8_gr_14dd1826:


    gr "Don't feel like you have to. If you burden yourself with guilt, you won't be able to excel at the things you normally do well..."


translate English day8_gr_8ec60b10:


    gr "The first time I tried to write a journal entry, it was a huge mess."


translate English day8_gr_8cdf295a:


    gr "I found myself with a stack of notebooks that I'd use for three days and then promptly abandon."


translate English day8_gr_759c94c4:


    pl "But you said that you wanted to see what was going through my mind."


translate English day8_gr_d5ebd193:


    gr "Regardless, you know I'm always thinking about you, [na2]."


translate English day8_gr_0309b6f4:


    nar "Liar."


translate English day8_gr_4dba65ea_1:


    gr "..."


translate English day8_gr_b574d0cb:


    gr "I'm really sorry about what happened yesterday. Doubting your symptoms and forcing you to disclose them to me..."


translate English day8_gr_ea7cd215:


    gr "I'm experienced enough to know such selfish tactics only produce negative results. My only excuse is I was very tired."


translate English day8_gr_c7f9b059:


    gr "I'm truly sorry."


translate English day8_gr_669bb0bf_2:


    nar "..."


translate English day8_gr_95f93237:


    pl "The negative result was directly caused by what you did?"


translate English day8_gr_33749993:


    gr "Huh? Not exactly... {w}Well, I've worked here long enough that I can't outright deny it..."


translate English day8_gr_94a3e974:


    pl "Be honest with me, Doc. You know I don't doubt your capabilities."


translate English day8_gr_ca98b555:


    gr "The problem is there are more people involved than just us. {w}And I can't go giving out information about my other patients without their permission."


translate English day8_gr_2aa293fc:


    pl "If you tell me how hard it was to deal with this other patient, I'll let it go."


translate English day8_gr_428c514d:


    gr "[na2]... It'd be rude and a breach of trust to admit that treating one of my patients was difficult."


translate English day8_gr_307004cb:


    pl "You won't condemn their character, will you?"


translate English day8_gr_877c5b84:


    gr "Of course not! But this is a different problem altogether. {w}Not because I don't trust you, but because it'd be akin to breaking a promise I made to myself."


translate English day8_gr_e4d6b4e4:


    pl "I want to know more about you, just like you're always saying you want to know more about me."


translate English day8_gr_8129d465:


    pl "And if we're to build a relationship based on trust, honesty becomes incredibly important, right?"


translate English day8_gr_8d42ccaa:


    gr "Trust..."


translate English day8_gr_486837fb:


    pl "I want to trust you, Doc. I won't tell anyone."


translate English day8_gr_4dba65ea_2:


    gr "..."


translate English day8_gr_7fc7bc71:


    gr "If you insist, [na2], then... okay."


translate English day8_gr_4d005841:


    nar "She takes a sip of her tea which is starting to cool. {w}Her gaze grows distant, as if lost in thought."


translate English day8_gr_25a1d7c5:


    gr "Let's see... It was around seven years ago. And yet even now, I find it hard to forget."


translate English day8_gr_5beedc5f:


    gr "No, more like, I can't let myself forget..."


translate English day8_gr_d3fa9b52:


    gr "It was shortly after I took my place as the auxiliary bishop. {w}I had already gotten used to working here in the temple,"


translate English day8_gr_c88c692b:


    gr "and was at the point where I was helping priests from other departments besides just the Health Department..."


translate English day8_gr_e9f397c4:


    gr "Actually, at the time, the Cleanup Department still didn't exist as its own entity. The Disposal Squad was a subdepartment within the Magic Department."


translate English day8_gr_b6484430:


    gr "The Cleanup Department the way it is now seems to be the catch-all for kids who don't seem to fit in anywhere else,"


translate English day8_gr_f8b0a4d8:


    gr "but back then, the Disposal Squad was made of mostly older folks just trying to make some extra money."


translate English day8_gr_eb4c5eb7:


    gr "Those folks... were pretty ordinary. {w}Mostly men who were two years older than me."


translate English day8_gr_be4c1d63:


    pl "Was the Disposal Squad back then in charge of the same tasks we do now?"


translate English day8_gr_97df11be:


    gr "Yes. Very similar... Taking care of corpses and dealing with The Lost..."


translate English day8_gr_e835f237:


    gr "Regardless of the passage of time, the job remains one that is difficult for most people to endure..."


translate English day8_gr_9f26ae95:


    gr "Yet it's a job that needs doing. And the people who work it look worse for wear because of it."


translate English day8_gr_3aa61f25:


    pl "What do you mean?"


translate English day8_gr_f3149a35:


    gr "Ha ha ha... You never miss anything, huh? {w}When this particular patient first came to me, it was due to problems with insomnia."


translate English day8_gr_e6ae8771:


    gr "He had trouble sleeping, and when he did, he was plagued by nightmares... So I gave him some sleep aids hoping they might help."


translate English day8_gr_ed4e3bec:


    gr "Yet a part of me couldn't accept that was his only problem... I was convinced the reason for his suffering lay somewhere else."


translate English day8_gr_2435fe51:


    gr "I'm ashamed to admit it, but I involved myself far more than I should have, and..."


translate English day8_gr_011f165c:


    pl "You asked to meet him for periodic counseling sessions?"


translate English day8_gr_db1c156e:


    gr "Yes. He was pretty reluctant from the get-go. {w}I know now that if someone truly requires assistance, they'll come to you without prompting."


translate English day8_gr_894e76d9:


    gr "But at the time, I felt like I needed to reach out, to show him I was here... Haha... I was so young and stupid."


translate English day8_gr_7a1d98ea:


    pl "You're not stupid, Doc."


translate English day8_gr_3bb6048c:


    gr "The thing about this guy is... He was depressed."


translate English day8_gr_f505226e:


    gr "Which is a natural enough reaction when you have to deal with corpses every day. Coming to grips with knowing the corpse you're disposing of was once alive..."


translate English day8_gr_fd0b5ac0:


    gr "It makes you aware of obvious things that most people don't really think about, like your own mortality."


translate English day8_gr_b59c97a3:


    gr "There are a lot of problems that crop up aside from the stress that's simply part of the job."


translate English day8_gr_2cbbfc9a:


    gr "Individually, these problems are quite trivial, but when they start to pile up, it becomes hard to ignore."


translate English day8_gr_8e567e2a:


    pl "Is it hard to treat folks with depression?"


translate English day8_gr_2db359c1:


    gr "It depends. Depression is like the common cold, in that everyone deals with it at some point. {w}Once you think it's gone, another problem crops up."


translate English day8_gr_c2084cee:


    gr "It's not something you need to hide! {w}In this case, it wasn't actually that difficult to deal with. {w}Unfortunately... he rejected the treatment."


translate English day8_gr_63ce2952:


    pl "Because he refused to admit he was sick?"


translate English day8_gr_e97aa02e:


    gr "You'd think so, huh? But it was actually the opposite."


translate English day8_gr_1900694a:


    gr "As I said before, it's only recently that mental illness has taken the forefront in the capital mainly due to everyone's dependence on beliefs of God and Pestis,"


translate English day8_gr_6a24c86b:


    gr "and yet there remains a stigma attached to it. {w}More so back then, actually. And this man was a devout follower of God."


translate English day8_gr_90de52f1:


    gr "He believed the illness being harbored in his psyche was due to the defilement of his soul by Pestis."


translate English day8_gr_a1bfa71e:


    gr "I did everything I could to convince him otherwise. {w}But he was convinced that there was no medicine nor therapy strong enough to remove the contamination of Pestis from within himself..."


translate English day8_gr_e6034073:


    gr "His work suffered as a result, but it also increased his religious zeal... {w}And finally..."


translate English day8_gr_ab42b371:


    pl "He killed himself?"


translate English day8_gr_5cd3a3fb:


    gr "..."


translate English day8_gr_a53b8556:


    nar "She looks pale, and her eyelids blink rapidly in succession as if she's awakening from her past memories. {w}Then she looks at me once again."


translate English day8_gr_178d31b7:


    gr "I'm glad you understand how I feel and acknowledge it, [na2]. {w}I was pretty conceited back then, and made many presumptions."


translate English day8_gr_1180cd99:


    gr "Forcing him to do things my way, getting involved with things that didn't concern me... I had no idea how toxic that type of behavior actually was."


translate English day8_gr_99ddf341:


    pl "Do you understand now?"


translate English day8_gr_a299c422:


    gr "Deep inside myself, yes. {w}But I still have a ways to go. Especially considering what happened yesterday..."


translate English day8_gr_19b3959f:


    gr "I apologize for talking about something that dark, [na2]. {w}You're probably disappointed in me, aren't you?"


translate English day8_gr_a703b11b:


    pl "Of course not. You did the best you could, Doc."


translate English day8_gr_eb91da1d:


    gr "Thank you..."


translate English day8_gr_8e189a92:


    nar "That's what anyone would have said to her. {w}Both back then and now."


translate English day8_gr_eec12d8f:


    gr "How did it go after you left?"


translate English day8_gr_619771ba:


    pl "Well enough. I meant it when I said I stopped having those dreams. I don't see anything weird anymore, and I don't have memory gaps either."


translate English day8_gr_a47a8ab9:


    gr "I'm glad to hear that... You were probably just suffering from stress. {w}I know how exhausting your line of work can be, [na2]."


translate English day8_gr_963eaaaa:


    pl "So you think the cause of all of my symptoms was simply stress?"


translate English day8_gr_b13a6512:


    gr "Stress may seem simple at first, but it can have a huge impact on a person's psyche."


translate English day8_gr_3e489811:


    gr "It's also why I told you how important it is to get your thoughts in order. {w}Because when pent-up stress finally explodes, terrible things can happen."


translate English day8_gr_dec040f1:


    pl "You were concerned because you didn't think I was handling my pent-up stress properly, right? {w}Do you still feel that way?"


translate English day8_gr_956c789b:


    gr "I still have no idea what exactly happened to you, [na2]... {w}Is it possible for you to tell me?"


translate English day8_gr_745ddb66:


    pl "I'm not sure if I can. But I wish I could."


translate English day8_gr_39368e7c:


    gr "Do you regret it?"


translate English day8_gr_f26fc263:


    pl "Not at all. Honestly, I feel almost rejuvenated. {w}It was the best feeling I've ever experienced in my entire life. I was equal to the task, and I did it."


translate English day8_gr_23ecaa33:


    pl "Honestly, the only thing holding me back thus far is stupidity, not rationality."


translate English day8_gr_28579c08:


    gr "But [na2]... You're going to have to face the people who assaulted you. Are you okay with that?"


translate English day8_gr_aedc4d56:


    pl "What they did was nothing more than an act of violence. {w}All it did was help show what kind of person I was and how it shaped me into who I am now."


translate English day8_gr_dd8fbdaa:


    pl "I don't want to live my life a perpetual loser."


translate English day8_gr_1c951a10:


    gr "I see... If that's how you feel, then there isn't really anything I can say..."


translate English day8_gr_59a56bac:


    gr "But [na2], I don't want you coming out of this experience thinking that violence and anger are ever the correct answer, no matter the problem."


translate English day8_gr_8edd6d8f:


    gr "Now that you've felt the satisfaction that comes with an act of violence, you'll look for an excuse to do so again. {w}What kind of person do you think you'll become if the pattern repeats itself?"


translate English day8_gr_eb1e660c_5:


    pl "..."


translate English day8_gr_7553c695:


    gr "Worst case scenario, you'll find yourself more monster than a man."


translate English day8_gr_f8028400:


    pl "Doc, who are you talking about?"


translate English day8_gr_a438b1ff:


    gr "Huh?"


translate English day8_gr_3563ac33:


    pl "I never said anything about getting into a fight. {w}In fact, I never once mentioned any kind of fight at all."


translate English day8_gr_5b014d77:


    pl "And yet you've clearly come to the assumed conclusion that I attacked someone."


translate English day8_gr_c7a038d6:


    gr "I swear you mentioned something like that..."


translate English day8_gr_f3b532eb:


    pl "Nope. You're the one who was caught up in memories of the past. Which is why you wanted me to regret what happened or feel remorseful, right?"


translate English day8_gr_4dba65ea_3:


    gr "..."


translate English day8_gr_dc43a8fd:


    pl "But, Doc. I don't regret anything. {w}Not even if they apologized."


translate English day8_gr_570684cd:


    pl "In fact, I don't think I did anything wrong. I wanted to do it, so I did."


translate English day8_gr_5cc4a628:


    pl "Because it was due to the build-up of stress you mentioned. Perhaps the sudden surge of emotions was more than I could handle."


translate English day8_gr_843308b9:


    pl "Either way, you were the source of the problem."


translate English day8_gr_83822d73:


    gr "[na2]... I'm not just saying this in hopes that you might change your mind."


translate English day8_gr_73a2c701:


    gr "I need you to know that what you did was wrong."


translate English day8_gr_10068d2f:


    pl "You think I don't know that?!" with sshake


translate English day8_gr_16ed2ab6:


    gr "If you know it, then shouldn't you come up with a better way to solve your problems? {w}Or do you plan on living the rest of your life with the same twisted sense of morality?!" with sshake


translate English day8_gr_eb1e660c_6:


    pl "..."


translate English day8_gr_690687fa:


    nar "We both sigh at the same time. {w}The tea that I never took a single sip of is soaking into my shoes and the cuff of my pants."


translate English day8_gr_d796ea8e:


    nar "I sit back down in my chair, hanging my head to avoid meeting her gaze."


translate English day8_gr_4479a161:


    gr "Look, [na2], I'm sorry for stressing you out. {w}If what I said was ambiguous enough that it led to a misunderstanding... then I apologize for that, too."


translate English day8_gr_e5eb9ce0:


    gr "I'd like to believe what you did was nothing more than an impulsive mistake. {w}That isn't out of the question for a kid your age."


translate English day8_gr_8ded0e14:


    gr "When you don't know how to deal with stress, it's all too easy to turn to violence."


translate English day8_gr_1119fce9:


    gr "I like you a lot, [na2], as both your doctor and friend."


translate English day8_gr_9b8180b7:


    gr "You mean a lot to me, which is why I don't want you straying from the path you're meant to be on. I'm not asking you to change your mind right away, but at least give it some thought..."


translate English day8_gr_d80730a4:


    pl "I love you, too, Doc!"


translate English day8_gr_a411445d:


    gr "..." with sshake


translate English day8_gr_299e4eb4:


    gr "...Did you really listen to what I had to say, [na2]?"


translate English day8_gr_ad8d5d57:


    pl "Of course. I'm glad you're being so honest with me. {w}It's nice knowing you feel the same way I do."


translate English day8_gr_78f560b5:


    gr "Can you pick up the cup that fell over?"


translate English day8_gr_9c414277:


    nar "She rubs at her eyes which are covered in a film of tears until they turn red."


translate English day8_gr_25765972:


    nar "The cup in question isn't for tea but one filled with milk she gave me when I first arrived."


translate English day8_gr_dff6a919:


    gr "What was the fight about anyways? You said you wanted to, but what even started it?"


translate English day8_gr_60b8c11f:


    pl "You still believe there was a reason behind it?"


translate English day8_gr_75b8ee87:


    gr "Of course... I know you, [na2]... {w}You're not the type of kid who'd resort to violence without a good reason."


translate English day8_gr_22ba480f:


    nar "I frown at the implication behind her spoken words, as if she's trying to make me accept responsibility for my own assault."


translate English day8_gr_b95f823f:


    pl "There was an argument and he shoved me first, but..."


translate English day8_gr_e629328c:


    nar "I find myself hesitating, unable to continue."


translate English day8_gr_59b1cf34:


    nar "It's not that I have trouble recounting the incident in question, but more that I don't really want to be the one to explain what happened."


translate English day8_gr_facc8251:


    pl "I was just... caught off guard. {w}In that moment, I couldn't believe someone around my own age would say something that stupid... And I knew her..."


translate English day8_gr_6438f892:


    gr "I can only imagine what a shock that must have been. {w}Rumors have a tendency to make people uneasy through the mere act of spreading them."


translate English day8_gr_186133d1:


    pl "It wasn't that I felt uneasy. Because at the end of the day, rumors are nothing more than hearsay from groundless sources."


translate English day8_gr_988fd981:


    pl "Honestly, I don't really care at this point what anyone has to say about me. {w}And I'm over what happened with that girl, thanks to you."


translate English day8_gr_88a7b543:


    pl "By the way, you probably feel differently regarding the rumor mill and your own reputation, huh?"


translate English day8_gr_e61fe6df:


    gr "What do you mean by that?"


translate English day8_gr_98e5ada6:


    nar "Her reaction causes me to roll my eyes."


translate English day8_gr_00fb74ed:


    pl "I can tell it bothers you a lot, right? {w}Why? {w}It's not like you're actually married."


translate English day8_gr_4dba65ea_4:


    gr "..."


translate English day8_gr_b5fb4344:


    pl "Am I wrong? As far as I know, none of the priests who work here in the temple are allowed to have a spouse,"


translate English day8_gr_8f2feca2:


    pl "so until you and the bishop retire, you aren't allowed to have a formal wedding ceremony."


translate English day8_gr_dc864613:


    gr "You're right. {w}It seems you've learned quite a lot regarding the rules here in the temple, [na2]. {w}But why does that matter?"


translate English day8_gr_2a20d95a:


    gr "Everyone here acknowledges our relationship regardless."


translate English day8_gr_26ee616a:


    gr "The reason why we continue to stay here is due to our dedication toward our jobs and our desire to focus on our profession and help others. {w}We'll have an official ceremony when the time is right."


translate English day8_gr_8716764e:


    pl "What do you mean by asking me why it matters? {w}I thought following the rules established within the temple was the be-all and end-all?"


translate English day8_gr_d7785014:


    pl "And here you are, a bishop and an auxiliary bishop, flaunting those same rules... You really think excuses like that will work simply because the other priests are okay with it?"


translate English day8_gr_0d2cfbbd:


    pl "You're too old to be playing house..."


translate English day8_gr_1c2ad1a1:


    gr "I understand what you're trying to say, [na2]. And I've thought long and hard about it."


translate English day8_gr_878ed32c:


    gr "But nonetheless, I want to keep working here in this position. And in order to be able to stand in front of you and your fellow priests..."


translate English day8_gr_cba915ec:


    gr "I came to an agreement with the cardinal. {w}But also, there's another more fundamental reason why I can't get married..."


translate English day8_gr_bb253a8e:


    pl "Because you're infertile?"


translate English day8_gr_4dba65ea_5:


    gr "..."


translate English day8_gr_572a48a2:


    gr "Exactly..."


translate English day8_gr_f0aa48f1:


    pl "Yeah? I'm glad I listened carefully to everything you had to say. {w}Anyways, I guess that means you're not married then, hrm?"


translate English day8_gr_4f24707a:


    gr "No... But I still love him."


translate English day8_gr_ffeda7ac:


    pl "Are you sure it's the man you love and not the work you do?"


translate English day8_gr_4dba65ea_6:


    gr "..."


translate English day8_gr_b1d58175:


    pl "You get off on saying your work is your life and you love everything about it. {w}Though it's obvious the only thing that motivates you is compliments and praise."


translate English day8_gr_f68b3c41:


    gr "You shouldn't pick on your elders..."


translate English day8_gr_0ca1de87:


    pl "No matter what happens, you do the best you can and somehow always come out as the victim."


translate English day8_gr_50d66b2b:


    pl "Considering your mistake this time was due to your own shortcomings, you naturally come to the conclusion that there's room for improvement."


translate English day8_gr_99ce32d9:


    pl "I know this because of how protective everyone is of you, Doc, which is mainly thanks to the benevolence you've cultivated simply by doing whatever you've wanted until now."


translate English day8_gr_a9e494e9:


    gr "Stop...!"


translate English day8_gr_8ef7bc14:


    pl "You're not interested in protecting your patients, Doc, but your job title."


translate English day8_gr_b42010b5:


    pl "When you send however many people to their deaths, you write it off by saying you did the best you could..."


translate English day8_gr_b2131dc9:


    gr "Stop! You're wrong! It's not like that at all!" with sshake


translate English day8_gr_160635ea:


    nar "..."


translate English day8_gr_74211002:


    pl "You startled me there, shouting like that... What's wrong?"


translate English day8_gr_78a211cb:


    gr "God... Rgh!!!"


translate English day8_gr_110bae46:


    pl "Doc? Are you okay? What's the matter with you? Hang on. Is there anything I can do?"


translate English day8_gr_563fb76a:


    gr "No! {w}No, [na2]. I'm fine... Don't! {w}Don't touch me! Please!" with sshake


translate English day8_gr_c15b2203:


    nar "She slumps forward, her slender shoulders trembling. The pupils in her wide-open eyes flit anxiously from side to side, her gaze distant and unfocused."


translate English day8_gr_b703f79b:


    nar "I doubt anyone else could've brought themselves to say that to her aside from myself. She's been living in ignorance until now."


translate English day8_gr_c85d598e:


    nar "A life where the people around you constantly protect you and praise you is akin to living with both eyes tightly closed."


translate English day8_gr_dcf89cee:


    nar "The proof of this lies in the fact that she has no clue there are people who hate her, that she never asks how someone is doing before meddling in their misfortune,"


translate English day8_gr_2a327314:


    nar "how unaware she seems to be of the fact that actions done in good faith but without considering the consequences are worse than those motivated by malice."


translate English day8_gr_2190c1ad:


    nar "I'm the one who removed that blindfold from over her eyes. Not herself, and not that man, but me. {w}And the first person she saw in this brand new world was also me."


translate English day8_gr_f3272e6c:


    nar "She looks at me, her gaze worn-out. {w}Finally, she faces me, the victim, as the perpetrator she so rightfully is."


translate English day8_gr_ddc039a7:


    gr "I'm sorry for shouting like that... {w}Did I scare you?"


translate English day8_gr_32b96f38:


    pl "Don't force yourself past what you can do. Drink your tea and try to calm down."


translate English day8_gr_a1ef1ed6:


    gr "No, [na2]... Enough. I swear I'm fine... I just feel terrible..."


translate English day8_gr_11584af6:


    pl "You're sure you don't need some time to calm down?"


translate English day8_gr_6b7b536a:


    gr "No. No way... I'm fine. {w}I swear I'm fine... You should be getting back, though, right? Hang on..."


translate English day8_gr_df3643ac:


    nar "She drags herself, still seemingly on edge, toward the bookcase. I hear the sound of a drawer opening and then the rustle of paper."


translate English day8_gr_84ac9512:


    nar "When she returns to her chair, she's holding what looks like an envelope."


translate English day8_gr_54325cd7:


    nar "She glances at me before sitting down. She's never side-eyed me like that before."


translate English day8_gr_8eafd460:


    gr "[na2], what I'm giving you is..."


translate English day8_gr_3880f9c1:


    pl "Medicine."


translate English day8_gr_19c989aa:


    gr "Yes, exactly. It's a pill you swallow. {w}It's enough for three days. Take one in the morning and one before you sleep, with water."


translate English day8_gr_5d2ba0ba:


    pl "Because sick people need medicine to get better, right?"


translate English day8_gr_2dc52ddc:


    gr "No... It's medicine to help you stay in the comfortable state you currently seem to be in."


translate English day8_gr_a0fce5d2:


    pl "So you're going to turn me into a junkie?"


translate English day8_gr_4d879bef:


    gr "Not only sick people take medicine, [na2]. It's also for people who want to lead a stable life."


translate English day8_gr_f8210d48:


    pl "My life is stable enough as it is! I'm not having nightmares, I'm not seeing hallucinations, my memories are fine..."


translate English day8_gr_5ab13cd2:


    gr "And yet you have no idea if or when you might relapse. You're in a very unstable mental state right now."


translate English day8_gr_2d77a020:


    gr "You need more than your own good intentions to make sure you stay safe."


translate English day8_gr_97fef2d2:


    pl "So you're saying I can't make it alone?"


translate English day8_gr_38772b9f:


    gr "I'm saying there are people who can and want to help you."


translate English day8_gr_e038f1f5:


    nar "I glare at her before eventually bowing my head."


translate English day8_gr_050d24ed:


    nar "It's not one of agreement, and yet she places the envelope of pills in my hand anyways."


translate English day8_gr_21d30bf4:


    gr "Thank you."


translate English day8_gr_eb1e660c_7:


    pl "..."


translate English day8_gr_9167c03b:


    gr "Take the rest of the day off. I'll be waiting for you to come back tomorrow."


translate English day8_gr_b0b1418e:


    pl "Seriously?"


translate English day8_gr_706f8878:


    gr "Of course..."


translate English day8_gr_f1fed625:


    nar "There's more I want to say, but I can't bring myself to do so right now. Because I can already picture in my head the look on her face after hearing it."


translate English day8_gr_7075f4b6:


    nar "I get to my feet and the moment I open the door, I hear the sound of chair legs scrapping the floor from behind me. {w}I suddenly relax my hand, spreading my fingers wide."


translate English day8_gr_7e4cd208:


    nar "There's some kind of crumbly, dried substance on my skin in the spaces between my fingers."


translate English day8_gr_7cb0ac7d:


    nar "I had forgotten about what happened this morning. It seems like lately, I've been forgetting things unintentionally."


translate English day8_gr_dc9a8eb3:


    nar "Because there are so many things that need my attention. {w}I can't even seem to recall the face of that girl who has tormented me for so long."


translate English day8_gr_6e883a2d:


    nar "It doesn't help that my memory of the incident itself is vague to begin with. I scratch my head, full of a mess of emotions, in agitation, and as I do so, I feel something odd sticking up from my scalp."


translate English day8_gr_127886b1:


    nar "I hesitantly look down at my hand only to discover a blackish-red substance attached to a clump of hair. A blood clot. {w}I stop abruptly in my tracks."


translate English day8_gr_394ef869:


    nar "A strange man I've never seen before is reflected in the window glass. He peers out at me from behind a mess of unkempt hair, his eyes blood-shot."


translate English day8_gr_d434f252:


    nar "There's dried blood on his chapped lips... {w}I can't even force out a laugh at the sight of how I look."


translate English day8_gr_c2a4ef4f:


    nar "I force my legs, which seem frozen to the floor, into motion, changing my trajectory away from the window."


translate English day8_gr_99c5fd59:


    nar "I could have gone forward or to the side, but I have a feeling I should go straight back the way I came."


translate English day8_gr_c3e4dc56:


    nar "Because the angel is there. {w}Of course she is."


translate English day8_gr_d87171ee:


    nar "Angels, by their nature, are not beings that can be sought out or called forth. They only visit those whose souls are on the brink of destruction..."


translate English day8_gr_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day8_gr_8691cfa0:


    "\n \"I don't really feel like going today. I feel like a certain sense of laziness or irregular conduct is justified given the circumstances. {w}I figured I wouldn't be in that much trouble despite this type of violent altercation."


translate English day8_gr_61b03da2:


    "In fact, I know I'll get away with what I did completely. {w}Or rather, I'm confident that the incident itself will be buried and forgotten away.\""


translate English day8_gr_ad4c1123:


    et "I'm sorry, but this really doesn't interest me in the slightest."


translate English day8_gr_e8184ec0:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Also, Grette told me this fascinating story about something that happened, what was it, seven years ago? About a priest, diagnosed with depression, who killed himself. {w}She expressed remorse, blaming herself for what happened, though I wasn't entirely convinced. {w}Of course I'm aware that person wasn't a bad guy."


translate English day8_gr_ee7498ab:


    et "It's more like she blames herself for some self-perceived shortcomings, viewing the incident as a necessary experience in life that one moves on from all the wiser... She doesn't even seem aware of her own reactions. {w}She believes she forced him onto the path that led to him taking his own life.\""


translate English day8_gr_7b7ec84b:



    nvl clear
    "\n The scene outside the window is mostly hidden by a deep fog following the rain. {w}As the sun peeks through the clouds, I talk to the angel, my face resting on the ground."


translate English day8_gr_4782873b:


    et "She listens silently to my sordid tale."


translate English day8_gr_06c7b8ff:



    nvl clear
    "\n The worst was when she forced me to swallow the pills. The smell reminded me of animal piss and I wanted to vomit as soon as I put them in my mouth. One of the pills wouldn't go down and ended up dissolving in the water, filling my mouth with an unbearable bitterness. {w}To make matters worse, the shape of the pills themselves caused them to get stuck in my parched esophagus, and I could feel them in there no matter how much water I drank."


translate English day8_gr_3170e7f5:


    et "Which is why I ended up getting into bed so late last night. I ultimately decided not to go to work today, and yet no one came to check on me. {w}I'm sure if he or anyone else stops by tomorrow, they'll blame me for what happened today. {w}But what exactly can they blame me for?"


translate English day8_gr_dcfde400:



    nvl clear
    "\n I find myself unable to think straight under the barrage of my constantly swirling emotions. {w}It's as if my brain is covered in a thick plastic film, preventing me from remembering anything."


translate English day8_gr_089e0909:


    et "But almost immediately after, an exhaustion blankets my being, and none of that seems to matter. {w}Perhaps it's the effects of the medicine. By the time I close my eyes, my thoughts had quieted down to silence."


translate English day8_gr_76b2fe88_3:


    nvl clear


translate English day9_gr_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day9_gr_a7bd0bfb:


    "\n I take the pills in the morning when I wake up and again at night before bed in a state of almost mindless apathy. {w}I have no desire to do so, and yet surprisingly enough, it's the first thing I remember as soon as I wake up."


translate English day9_gr_422b61b4:


    "It's quiet outside, and my head hurts. That's a pretty bad sign. Did I accidentally sleep in?"


translate English day9_gr_f770d2ec:


    et "I open the door and at the same time, I hear a faint sound. It's one I'm not used to hearing. {w}The sound of paper fluttering in the wind."


translate English day9_gr_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day9_gr_d5119c60:


    "\n The paper in question is pinned to a gap in the old door. {w}The first thing I see is Securett's name written on it. Just that alone is enough to fill me with revulsion. He must have figured I wasn't going to open the door, so he left the note before going on ahead."


translate English day9_gr_b195c44c:


    et "\"No need to rush, but if you can't make it to work, you'll need to get a doctor's note from the infirmary.\" {w}I read the words printed on that scrap of paper through bleary eyes before closing the door."


translate English day9_gr_15d9a470:



    nvl clear
    "\n A doctor's note? {w}I thought something weird was up yesterday, but I guess they've been planning on making me out to be a psycho all along. Which is why I suddenly need a note... He must have noticed my frequent visits to the infirmary from the very beginning. No doubt about it."


translate English day9_gr_e932db2c:


    et "Or is it possible Dr. Grette tipped him off?"


translate English day9_gr_cb3c7ff8:


    nar "I leave the dorms and head down the hall instead of taking the stairs. {w}I'm on my way to the infirmary instead of the department office, which is where he wanted me to go."


translate English day9_gr_a7ef0daf:


    cr "Oh, gosh! If it isn't Lord [na] from the Cleanup Department!"


translate English day9_gr_3821fbdc:


    pl "And you are none other than...?"


translate English day9_gr_6e42602a:


    cr "Stop it! As one of Saint Sheol's benefactors, I help procure necessary supplies for the Cleanup Department. I'm also the eldest daughter of the proud Myosotis family,"


translate English day9_gr_fabc0a28:


    cr "Clione Myosotis! {w}Otherwise known as Claire. Has it been long enough that you forgot who I am?"


translate English day9_gr_7c11367a:


    nar "Oh, I remember this noisy, nosy girl well enough, an image of her chirping away incessantly like a bird begging for food still clear in my mind."


translate English day9_gr_ed932ae2:


    pl "Aha, right. Of course. It has been a while, huh?"


translate English day9_gr_be8bccc6:


    cr "Exactly one week and two days! {w}What can I say, Lord [na]? You seem to have come a long way since the last time I saw you..."


translate English day9_gr_7d3e3f66:


    cr "It looks like you lost weight. Are you doing okay?"


translate English day9_gr_dccd805c:


    pl "Work's been tough, but why are you here again? Another procurement of supplies?"


translate English day9_gr_300d4fd1:


    cr "Actually, I only bring those once a month... Today, I'm here on business."


translate English day9_gr_f8307133:


    cr "Well, in the capacity of my position as a volunteer, that is. You could say I'm a priest in training."


translate English day9_gr_309f52d0:


    pl "Isn't it all the same thing either way?"


translate English day9_gr_b906b835:


    cr "I'm sure you're probably wondering what exactly I'm here to do, hrm?"


translate English day9_gr_84c8ade1:


    pl "Not really, no..."


translate English day9_gr_482ce9f2:


    cr "For your information, I'm helping out in the Health Department!"


translate English day9_gr_3a8d4a04:


    pl "The Health Department...?"


translate English day9_gr_863fb896:


    cr "Yes! I'll be here three times this week. {w}Nothing that exciting, mainly just helping with organizing paperwork..."


translate English day9_gr_15ec1c49:


    cr "brewing delicious tea, hanging up freshly laundered clothing to dry and whatnot. Stuff like that."


translate English day9_gr_e7bcd344:


    cr "But it's pretty helpful to the folks in the department. I'm actually just about to go on break."


translate English day9_gr_fd603562:


    pl "Is Grette... Ah, I mean, the doctor inside?"


translate English day9_gr_5842096b:


    cr "Hm... No. I'm pretty sure she's still in the hospital ward. Everyone seems to be on duty right now."


translate English day9_gr_4292e5a4:


    cr "Speaking of which, what exactly are you up to, Lord [na2]?"


translate English day9_gr_ff1d6bad:


    pl "I'm also on break..."


translate English day9_gr_a59a19a4:


    cr "A priest in training, such as yourself, from the Cleanup Department, {w}on break before noon? That's somewhat unusual. Most folks who finish a job tend to keep going..."


translate English day9_gr_ead83fe4:


    pl "What people do and when they do it is, quite frankly, none of your business."


translate English day9_gr_1c47c6ee:


    pl "More importantly, do you usually talk to people like that? {w}Or is it a habit you picked up from the Health Department?"


translate English day9_gr_5f365d8c:


    cr "I'm sorry? The air between us feels a lot different from the first time we met."


translate English day9_gr_fcd196a0:


    cr "Hrm, I see... I'm sure you have your reasons, which are completely valid. {w}I apologize if I offended you in some way."


translate English day9_gr_be3a7b98:


    cr "I enjoy gathering information on the goings-on within the temple, which leads me to be somewhat inquisitive."


translate English day9_gr_448f3c8b:


    pl "Information? So in other words, you collect rumors? {w}I feel like your reputation precedes you... In that case, are you to blame for the gossip running wild through the temple halls?"


translate English day9_gr_f64bad4b:


    cr "You seem to think I'm far more influential than I truly am. {w}The folks here in the temple love to gossip."


translate English day9_gr_8a2335d1:


    cr "There are enough rumors to go around that it'd be impossible for me to make them all up myself!"


translate English day9_gr_702aa603:


    cr "I love talking about them. Or was there a specific one you had in mind?"


translate English day9_gr_8c9329ee:


    pl "What's your opinion on Grette, the auxiliary bishop?"


translate English day9_gr_f7702443:


    cr "Dr. Grette? I honestly never would have expected you to take an interest in her over another lady..."


translate English day9_gr_9dcf0806:


    pl "What do you mean by that?"


translate English day9_gr_7430d0cb:


    cr "Nothing bad, of course. It's just that the day I met you, Lord [na2], I noticed you had your eye on Maya..."


translate English day9_gr_851d919c:


    pl "You talk way too much, you know that?"


translate English day9_gr_e18a6a9c:


    cr "Huh? {w}I, um... I'm just surprised, that's all. Unfortunately, the information I have is limited..."


translate English day9_gr_a9704b67:


    cr "So I deeply apologize. {w}You're not mad, are you?"


translate English day9_gr_acd9f13f:


    pl "I just want to know how she's been doing lately. I'm sure that your paths must cross frequently if you're working within the same department, right?"


translate English day9_gr_50f87171:


    cr "Dr. Grette is always so kind, is nice to everyone, but is also serious enough that even the slightest wrongdoing can't escape her notice."


translate English day9_gr_bc6e918d:


    cr "I owe quite a lot to her, in fact. They weren't joking about upholding her as an example to the priests in the temple."


translate English day9_gr_9af3e044:


    cr "But... Well, she certainly has seemed far from her usual cheerful self these past few days."


translate English day9_gr_1a949dd9:


    pl "She seems unwell, huh?"


translate English day9_gr_2f2bd8a1:


    nar "The reason why is obvious. She's worried about me."


translate English day9_gr_643c34e7:


    nar "She's a therapist whose job is to listen to other people's problems, but she herself lacks someone who will listen to hers."


translate English day9_gr_cbe43e8c:


    nar "Her appearance as an adult along with certain things she must keep guarded continue to exist within the shell of her being."


translate English day9_gr_7ef04cf7:


    cr "That's actually the reason why I'm here."


translate English day9_gr_825043cf:


    pl "I'm sorry?"


translate English day9_gr_d26a6102:


    cr "You see, I've been talking with Dr. Grette for some time now."


translate English day9_gr_a2d96ecc:


    cr "She listens to my everyday problems and treats them with a great deal of care, taking them seriously."


translate English day9_gr_65c9ad18:


    cr "She's been doing so, not just yesterday and today, but for the past several months. {w}With that said, I've refused to take her advice."


translate English day9_gr_5d60e9af:


    cr "I can't go into detail about what exactly... but I get the feeling she was hurt by that. My refusal to do so hurt her feelings..."


translate English day9_gr_4d9fbf0e:


    nar "She stands there, trembling, her tiny hands clasped together in concern. {w}Seeing her like that makes my heart skip a beat."


translate English day9_gr_f364a6af:


    pl "I'm certain it has nothing to do with you. {w}The doctor has... a lot on her plate."


translate English day9_gr_5b57aeb5:


    cr "Of course you're right. {w}When you're dealing with so much all at the same time, it can quickly become a huge burden to bear."


translate English day9_gr_112d5c7f:


    cr "And I know I've contributed to it. {w}At least a small part of the emotional damage she's dealing with is my fault."


translate English day9_gr_1801d530:


    nar "Her hands continue shaking. Grette seems to care for a lot of people, not just me."


translate English day9_gr_eda5220b:


    nar "I'm sure in her eyes, I'm nothing more than one of her many patients who need to be looked after."


translate English day9_gr_4ac16c57:


    nar "The moment that fact is seared into my brain, I'm overwhelmed by a surge of chaotic emotions."


translate English day9_gr_0cf79a13:


    pl "How long has this been going on?"


translate English day9_gr_22f966f0:


    cr "Yes? {w}Hrm, let's see... What's today again? I'm pretty sure she's been this way for three days now."


translate English day9_gr_4ff83ebd:


    nar "That definitely checks out."


translate English day9_gr_dc1281a3:


    pl "I see..."


translate English day9_gr_e3e8c00d:


    nar "She seems miserable as she looks up at me, but I simply walk off without saying goodbye."


translate English day9_gr_e5e31c4f:


    nar "At the very least, it doesn't sound like the doctor's told anyone about me."


translate English day9_gr_f563c26b:


    nar "Why would she? She's the great doctor that everyone trusts."


translate English day9_gr_42dc13d9:


    nar "The same person who is unable to confide in anyone else, but must bear the burden of blame from their own patients until they die."


translate English day9_gr_74ca010c:


    nar "Though, to be fair, this is a burden she voluntarily accepted and not one forced upon her, which I'm sure she's well aware of."


translate English day9_gr_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day9_gr_14a03aaa:


    "\n The infirmary is only slightly warm when I arrive, as if the heater has only just recently been turned on. The faint scent of tea wafts through the air."


translate English day9_gr_5f775b82:


    "The smell of sweet butter and baking bread that used to permeate the infirmary as far back as I can remember has gradually begun to dissipate since she stopped making sweets."


translate English day9_gr_cd211e07:


    "Yet the doctor herself remains as if guarding her domain, and she turns in her chair to face me as soon as I step inside. She looks tired."


translate English day9_gr_e5379368:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"You're here early.\""


translate English day9_gr_df952eb7:


    "\"If you're tired, why not drink something like coffee instead of tea?\""


translate English day9_gr_d13f7e82:


    "\"I can't quite explain it... but this feels just right.\""


translate English day9_gr_9d412f5b:



    nvl clear
    "\n Grette isn't the type of person who doesn't seem to care about what she wears, where she sleeps, or even whether she puts on make-up or not, but one thing she is particular about is what goes in her mouth. {w}Instead of avoiding food that's bad for her, she tends to avoid foods that are seen as bad by the other people around her."


translate English day9_gr_3cb5f554:


    "The only pastries and breads she eats are made up of flour, butter, and sugar."


translate English day9_gr_b4ddf800:


    "As if she feels she needs to be some kind of role model. {w}And even if no one else is aware of that, she's always known. All it takes is a modicum of restraint on her part to get a pat on the back from herself."


translate English day9_gr_8732d886:


    "Clearly tired, she stretches one arm over her head while yawning. Her white front teeth peek out from her mouth as she does so."


translate English day9_gr_303587da:


    "You look tired, I tell her, and she pats me on the shoulder as if in acknowledgment of my statement."


translate English day9_gr_f948995a:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"I am. It seems like I've been carting around supplies all morning...\""


translate English day9_gr_d7404ba2:


    "\"Really? You should have asked me to help.\""


translate English day9_gr_f80afa74:


    "\"I can handle that much. I'm not ready for the nursing home yet.\""


translate English day9_gr_fe18d770:



    nvl clear
    "\n Despite her best efforts, she's not someone I would consider fit. Whether due to her brush with Pestis when she was young or simply genetics, she's lacked a certain degree of stamina for the majority of her life."


translate English day9_gr_d5f73c93:


    "It's not a serious problem, and it'd probably be to her benefit to play it up, but instead, she goes to great lengths in order to hide this specific disadvantage. {w}I get the feeling she feels a certain amount of comfort and satisfaction from still being able to do things herself. I guess stubbornness isn't age-restricted."


translate English day9_gr_41d23afc:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"How have you been doing lately?\""


translate English day9_gr_28ecb616:


    "I purposefully ask her a question I know she wasn't expecting, and she averts her gaze in response, seemingly uneasy. {w}I don't get the impression she's trying to think up an excuse. Our eyes meet as she moistens her dry throat with tea, and she smiles back, a small wrinkle between her brows as if embarrassed over the truth."


translate English day9_gr_881192b0:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Not the best.\""


translate English day9_gr_eef2d166:


    "\"That's what happens when you push yourself too hard.\""


translate English day9_gr_d9f3fe9a:


    et "I know she usually doesn't like that type of response. {w}But today, she simply nods, murmuring that I'm probably right. I'm one of a select few she can be open and honest with about how she truly feels."


translate English day9_gr_c4c0d1a1:



    nvl clear
    "\n She carefully talks about what's troubling her, though it never ends with her merely complaining about the problem in question, instead leading to introspection of what's really going on."


translate English day9_gr_0d518449:


    "She finds it difficult to gain trust from the other priests. {w}Despite how much they like her, they never seem to come to her with their problems. No matter what she tells them, they always end up struggling with the same issues... And so on."


translate English day9_gr_901392ba:


    "They don't ask her for help because they lack the power or ability to do so. It's her duty as a doctor to understand their background and how their minds work. Nothing can be solved if she alone is the only one passionate about solving their problems."


translate English day9_gr_84ea527c:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Maybe I'm just bad at being a therapist...\""


translate English day9_gr_939b0069:


    "Of course she doesn't mean that. It's just a small amount of doubt or anxiety peeking through. {w}All it takes at a time like this is a simple word of encouragement or a pat on the back to cheer her right up."


translate English day9_gr_4826d9ae:


    "If I try to give her some advice, will she pretend to be mad at me for assuming her role as a therapist? Or will she laugh at the audacity of me trying to do so?"


translate English day9_gr_7322aa17:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Do you want me to compliment you, Grette?\""


translate English day9_gr_80c66c44:


    "I end up choosing neither. An odd expression crosses her face in response to my somewhat unexpected question as she studies me closely for a moment, trying to come up with some amusing response."


translate English day9_gr_2906889b:


    "And then a smile crosses her face. It's clear I've taken the conversation in a far different direction than what she'd been expecting."


translate English day9_gr_76b2fe88_3:


    nvl clear


translate English day9_gr_c18aaa71:


    et "\n \"What kind of compliment?\""


translate English day9_gr_76b2fe88_4:


    nvl clear


translate English day9_gr_3584f91f:


    pl "Haaah haaah..."


translate English day9_gr_94c90a30:


    nar "The strength drains from my body. The spot between my neck and my ear feels like it's on fire with heat."


translate English day9_gr_3554052b:


    nar "The empty infirmary is still only mildly warm, and there's no sign of anyone in the hallway outside."


translate English day9_gr_026c1cc2:


    nar "I can hear the sound of someone's footsteps from somewhere off in the distance. The bed in front of me is bathed in white light coming in through the gaps in the window curtain."


translate English day9_gr_a4798033:


    nar "The blanket lays crumpled around my knees."


translate English day9_gr_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day9_gr_dea55be2:


    nar "A corpse. For the first time in my life, I touched a corpse. It's far colder and more bloated than any living thing could possibly feel."


translate English day9_gr_bcac520e:


    nar "With my mouth shut tight and my brow furrowed, I stuff the body inside my sack."


translate English day9_gr_84baff37:


    nar "The last time I touched a hot human body, it looked like it was melting away."


translate English day9_gr_49ff96a3:


    nar "The clammy skin was drenched all over with sweat, as if the body itself was on fire."


translate English day9_gr_3a2f5921:


    nar "It could no longer form coherent sentences, probably because its brain had already melted away. And although it still looked vaguely like a body, it was soft and flabby."


translate English day9_gr_b678ede1:


    nar "In the cold, dark bathroom, the cool water overflows the basin, pouring down around my feet. {w}I feel stupid for admitting it, but I miss the warmth of another person."


translate English day9_gr_2c85aa54:


    nar "When I return to the infirmary, it feels different than usual."


translate English day9_gr_e2c4cab6:


    nar "The atmosphere is so thick, you could slice it with a knife, and through the gap in the door that's just slightly ajar, I hear a rustling sound. {w}And a woman's high-pitched voice... Grette's."


translate English day9_gr_fcfe4268:


    nar "It's getting increasingly louder, to the point where I can easily hear it from the hall. She's arguing with someone."


translate English day9_gr_40f2f3d7:


    gr "Can't you at least talk about it? Or consider how I feel?!"


translate English day9_gr_b1d758ed:


    gr "What exactly do you think you can do for that poor kid? I... {w}If you don't do something, I will!"


translate English day9_gr_9e2275cd:


    nar "Is she talking about me?"


translate English day9_gr_83ce2512:


    gr "You're always like this! You never change!"


translate English day9_gr_218caf6a:


    gr "Stop! I've heard enough... Don't say that!"


translate English day9_gr_8dbb711d:


    gr "...!"


translate English day9_gr_850010ed:


    gr "I'm sorry, [na2]. I know you stopped by to see me... {w}But unfortunately, I have some urgent business to attend to..."


translate English day9_gr_47d67a6e:


    pl "What kind of business?"


translate English day9_gr_9e2339bd:


    gr "I just got an urgent call. I need to go right now."


translate English day9_gr_7d98030b:


    pl "But you'll be back, right?"


translate English day9_gr_a10f5f6a:


    gr "Yes, but... I'll see you tomorrow, okay? I'm really sorry... {w}Don't forget to take your medicine, okay?"


translate English day9_gr_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "..."


translate English day9_gr_114b550b:


    nar "She briefly inquires about me while walking past without waiting for an answer. {w}I simply watch her walk out of sight without saying a word."


translate English day9_gr_2c9a5202:


    nar "With the door left wide open, I catch a whiff of a musky scent that seems completely out of place in the infirmary. It's the smell of cigarettes which I'm pretty familiar with at this point."


translate English day9_gr_bfb4669d:


    nar "Meaning that guy is inside right now."


translate English day9_gr_7b3505ec:


    nar "He sits in her usual spot, slumped down in her chair, seemingly out of sorts."


translate English day9_gr_08f86d70:


    nar "As soon as he notices me, though, he immediately straightens up."


translate English day9_gr_c8d9e6af:


    gg "So we meet again."


translate English day9_gr_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "..."


translate English day9_gr_188aab3b:


    gg "Still not a huge fan of me, huh?"


translate English day9_gr_f6f278a6:


    pl "Well, all you ever do is stink the infirmary up with your cigarettes despite the fact people are constantly coming and going through here."


translate English day9_gr_17bccee2:


    gg "...So that's a no."


translate English day9_gr_d6a58dda:


    nar "He exhales deeply and a cloud of white smoke floats up into the air from his nose and mouth."


translate English day9_gr_2ff2c2c8:


    nar "I make a point of coughing loudly while frowning in order to show my displeasure. {w}It feels almost like there's dust in my lungs."


translate English day9_gr_25d17052:


    gg "Want a smoke?"


translate English day9_gr_d3c26bf8:


    pl "No thanks."


translate English day9_gr_6236e1c4:


    gg "I was a pretty heavy smoker back when I was your age, you know."


translate English day9_gr_6df820bd:


    nar "He never wastes a chance to make fun of me."


translate English day9_gr_7c4974f7:


    pl "That's great, but I don't smoke. Dr. Grette hates it."


translate English day9_gr_4047a407:


    nar "I try to imagine the taste of tobacco, a substance I've never tried before. {w}I can feel the imaginary flavor fill my mouth."


translate English day9_gr_ec6a08d7:


    nar "I'm trying to provoke him in my own way, but all he does is pull an ashtray from the corner of the desk toward him, seemingly unperturbed."


translate English day9_gr_3360bb64:


    nar "That ashtray is a constant eyesore."


translate English day9_gr_d3f2ae52:


    nar "That Grette, who hates cigarettes, always leaves it there on her desk is proof enough that this man is constantly present in her thoughts."


translate English day9_gr_d842d373:


    pl "Did you two have a fight?"


translate English day9_gr_28ba92da:


    gg "You heard us, huh? {w}I guess it would be weird if you hadn't, considering the shouting at all."


translate English day9_gr_c994a471:


    pl "The way you are as a person pisses her off."


translate English day9_gr_0f4df04a:


    gg "I'm just doing my job."


translate English day9_gr_7eae5d9c:


    pl "What the hell does that even mean?!" with sshake


translate English day9_gr_9621ef4a:


    gg "What exactly do you have to yell about?"


translate English day9_gr_27d0d918:


    pl "I know more about your own wife than you do, to the point where you can't even see she's struggling."


translate English day9_gr_6a4d7cca:


    gg "Oh yeah? {w}Well, I appreciate your concern."


translate English day9_gr_eb1e660c_3:


    pl "..."


translate English day9_gr_e2a9c9ba:


    nar "He tears off a scrap of toilet paper, pours a few drops of water on it, and places it inside the ashtray. I take a deep breath in before releasing it, trying to reign in my emotions."


translate English day9_gr_043505ab:


    nar "He's trying to make me mad."


translate English day9_gr_176cb4e8:


    nar "And getting angry right now would only prove that I'm on edge."


translate English day9_gr_26861a97:


    pl "You think you're so great simply because you've known her longer than anyone else, huh?"


translate English day9_gr_157e950f:


    gg "What exactly am I bragging about again?"


translate English day9_gr_b0ecaece:


    pl "Your assumption that Dr. Grette will stay with you, no matter what."


translate English day9_gr_c1b67aaf:


    pl "No... Thinking she adores you is basically the same thing."


translate English day9_gr_5008bb71:


    pl "Do you honestly believe the only reason she spends so much time with you is because she cares for you?"


translate English day9_gr_3c60b4e4:


    pl "It's not like she has anywhere else she can go, and you are the bishop of her department."


translate English day9_gr_b0f11f81:


    gg "You're saying it's all a matter of circumstance related to environment inductive to the work she wants to do?"


translate English day9_gr_eb1e660c_4:


    pl "..."


translate English day9_gr_84b6efd8:


    gg "I know it's hard for you to understand right now, but it's actually fairly common for couples to prioritize their work above their partner. We're just up front about doing so."


translate English day9_gr_1198c723:


    gg "Your viewpoint on what constitutes a relationship isn't the only right one, you know."


translate English day9_gr_39c47e3b:


    pl "So you don't care at all about her comfort?"


translate English day9_gr_c9a705fe:


    gg "Is that what she likes?"


translate English day9_gr_dfbdbbbc:


    pl "Clearly not, according to you."


translate English day9_gr_8b8fb3e3:


    nar "He snuffs out his cigarette, seemingly unperturbed by my comment. {w}The burning embers sizzling out in the ashtray sound almost like mocking laughter."


translate English day9_gr_6f910f92:


    gg "You're probably curious what the fight was about, hrm?"


translate English day9_gr_567dfd01:


    pl "Not really, no..."


translate English day9_gr_2f559b8d:


    gg "We don't usually fight about personal matters. {w}The only time she ever gets that worked up is when it concerns a third party."


translate English day9_gr_7a04019f:


    gg "Grette always takes pride in her work, which naturally leads to her getting a bit..."


translate English day9_gr_40d193bd:


    gg "...overprotective of her patients. Even long after they've left her care."


translate English day9_gr_3895705e:


    nar "I don't want to hear any more."


translate English day9_gr_743070e2:


    nar "If the reason why she refuses to abandon me is simply because she sees me as a patient that she feels obligated to take care of,"


translate English day9_gr_9790ba09:


    nar "then that must mean there are dozens of other people she views in the same light as myself. That I'm not special at all."


translate English day9_gr_ca98a7af:


    nar "Which is why I told him I wasn't interested, but him continuing the conversation brought the fears I'd been purposefully avoiding to light."


translate English day9_gr_9aca4fa6:


    gg "I should get going... but do you have any other questions?"


translate English day9_gr_5d8c536b:


    pl "Do you know what's been bothering Dr. Grette so much lately?"


translate English day9_gr_80bd9c9c:


    gg "Most likely something work-related."


translate English day9_gr_4558663d:


    nar "And with that final statement, he slowly leaves the room. {w}The lingering indents in the cushion of his recently vacated chair prove that he'd sat there."


translate English day9_gr_3b8814a3:


    nar "I'd been planning on telling him exactly how sincere my feelings of love were for Grette."


translate English day9_gr_04b04e47:


    nar "And yet I knew he would simply file away my forthright confession as something naively juvenile,"


translate English day9_gr_653ef607:


    nar "akin to a student's adoration of their teacher. Repeating his words would only make me miserable."


translate English day9_gr_d2a5300a:


    nar "Of course, the thing that makes me feel most miserable of all is the fact that she's not here right now."


translate English day9_gr_e33d3276:


    nar "I can see the image of her, in profile, as she walked past me earlier on her way from the infirmary."


translate English day9_gr_1f576db9:


    nar "She was looking straight ahead. {w}She didn't spare me, who was right there, a second glance. Her eyes were focused on someone else."


translate English day9_gr_39455421:


    nar "Why?"


translate English day9_gr_6ce0f422:


    nar "Can I chalk up my psychopathic tendencies not even guaranteeing me a front row seat to her affection, let alone allowing me to replace that man, to me simply not being an adult yet?"


translate English day9_gr_42994e7d:


    nar "I step behind her desk. I open every drawer I can see, my eyes randomly skimming the neat stacks of paperwork kept inside."


translate English day9_gr_6817c8e0:


    nar "Dust motes float into the air, glittering around the edges of my vision."


translate English day9_gr_09d0d41a:


    nar "I'm not surprised to see a pack of cigarettes tucked away into the bottom most drawer. {w}After hastily stuffing them inside my pocket, I tidy up the mess I left behind."


translate English day9_gr_4acabda3:


    nar "I can feel my heart hammering frantically in my chest as I do so, and yet the doctor is still nowhere to be seen even after I shut the door to the infirmary behind me."


translate English day9_gr_6a63b3a0:


    nar "I always thought of cigarette smoke as something old-fashioned and putrid, but I realize it's actually sour with a hint of sweetness."


translate English day9_gr_f1fd5c2d:


    nar "It's a distinctive odor, like dried nuts. {w}I head over to the workplace, my hand constantly fiddling with the box in my pocket."


translate English day9_gr_e0ab62e5:


    nar "There's no point in stealing something just to hold onto it."


translate English day9_gr_9058fc24:


    nar "I'm going to need a source of heat if I want to light them, and there's always spare matches in the workplace."


translate English day9_gr_4319cb11:


    nar "The tip of the cigarette begins glowing orange as soon as I light it on fire. {w}As I shake out the lit match, I place the cigarette itself between my trembling lips, trying not to accidentally extinguish the flame."


translate English day9_gr_a2265469:


    nar "The paper itself doesn't taste all that bitter. {w}The problem starts the moment I inhale."


translate English day9_gr_1e1e4b73:


    pl "Cough! Cough cough!!!" with sshake


translate English day9_gr_b9b444ce:


    nar "Something catches in my throat, causing me to choke in response."


translate English day9_gr_9cc9ab91:


    nar "Acrid smoke pours from my mouth and nose. The pain from the smoke in my throat causes me to cough uncontrollably."


translate English day9_gr_304d054b:


    nar "I grab my throat as I try to force air out of my lungs, but it only makes things worse. The sudden rush of oxygen up through my windpipe only increases the pain in my throat, making it more difficult for me to breathe."


translate English day9_gr_2eb2d005:


    nar "Tears pour from my bloodshot eyes. I'm coughing so hard that I feel like I might vomit."


translate English day9_gr_984fcba2:


    nar "I feel more miserable than ever as I stand there in the dark warehouse, my face covered in tears and snot."


translate English day9_gr_f474d73d:


    nar "It's not long before I begin to feel lightheaded."


translate English day9_gr_4b7fc0b8:


    nar "I'm hit with a burst of exhaustion. I feel weak and dizzy. {w}The moment I pull the cigarette from my mouth, I'm overcome by uneasiness."


translate English day9_gr_863c8acb:


    nar "The type of nausea one might feel when hungover gradually builds inside me, either due to my prolonged bout of dizziness or the smoke itself."


translate English day9_gr_d24da577:


    pl "Ugh... Hack..."


translate English day9_gr_409b0466:


    nar "I end up tossing the cigarette to the floor, crushing it under my shoe while spitting out phlegm. A thin wisp of smoke escapes through the open door."


translate English day9_gr_e9329db6:


    nar "I'm actually in a pretty good mood. {w}I wonder if there's some kind of technique to inhaling?"


translate English day9_gr_c7db01ee:


    pl "...?"


translate English day9_gr_05e52af4:


    nar "I'm suddenly interrupted by the sound of a familiar cart accompanied by an equally familiar face."


translate English day9_gr_ac3ccf22:


    nar "As soon as he spots me, he walks over while calling out to me."


translate English day9_gr_ec488667:


    sc "I don't often see you around here at this time of the day."


translate English day9_gr_48489a1e:


    pl "It's not really that bizarre. I'm still a priest in the Cleanup Department, at least for now."


translate English day9_gr_79874dec:


    sc "Well... I guess. {w}Doing anything worthwhile?"


translate English day9_gr_b533da39:


    pl "Shut up... I already did what I had to do..."


translate English day9_gr_f9f3c2fc:


    sc "Great. {w}I feel like I made a superfluous observation."


translate English day9_gr_c19a0cba:


    pl "Look, it's none of your damn business. Leave me alone."


translate English day9_gr_030dd942:


    sc "Sure..."


translate English day9_gr_eb1e660c_5:


    pl "..."


translate English day9_gr_3d7edd2e:


    sc "What?"


translate English day9_gr_fa5d0156:


    pl "Do you smoke?"


translate English day9_gr_05ad539b:


    sc "Huh? Where'd that come from?"


translate English day9_gr_eda43029:


    pl "It's just... well... Just wondering how it works."


translate English day9_gr_0229ba0c:


    sc "Are you...?"


translate English day9_gr_77791284:


    sc "..."


translate English day9_gr_1707435b:


    sc "You know what? Never mind. {w}It's almost evening already. Make sure you head on back before it gets too late."


translate English day9_gr_eb1e660c_6:


    pl "..."


translate English day9_gr_95e590f4:


    pl "Ha!" with sshake


translate English day9_gr_8e22e4b3:



    nvl clear
    "\n Hahaha! Once he walks off, I suddenly burst into somewhat forced laughter. I feel heat coming from my throat which is still painfully raw."


translate English day9_gr_273fb129:


    "I'm such an idiot for even asking that dumb kid from the Cleanup Department whose only skill in life is pushing the carts to and fro."


translate English day9_gr_91167bae:


    "Knowing his fear of fire, he'd probably give up well before getting to the actual smoking part. {w}That's probably why he was acting so pretentious."


translate English day9_gr_d9bdc7ee:


    "Instead of admitting he couldn't smoke, he made it seem like a conscious choice to not engage in so-called bad behavior. Like he's some Beacon of Light and the rest of us are idiots."


translate English day9_gr_a0aff05b:


    et "All he ever does is treat us like kids who'll never grow up while he alone is the only mature adult..."


translate English day9_gr_bcb71007:



    nvl clear
    "\n Fuck! FUCK!" with sshake


translate English day9_gr_dd59050b:


    "But I'm different--because the angel chose me."


translate English day9_gr_8695afde:


    "In that hole where the milk of life will soon flow, the angel emits warmth and the unique scent of death that reminds us of our mortality,"


translate English day9_gr_5047cb55:


    et "and yet I'm the only one who can hear her voice as she spreads her dazzling wings to bless me with her blindingly bright light."


translate English day9_gr_1125dadd:



    nvl clear
    "\n I wrap my arms around her slender shoulders, nuzzling up to her breasts. She will stay by my side in this filthy world."


translate English day9_gr_6be1f77c:


    "And as long as she protects my soul, all my sins will be forgiven."


translate English day9_gr_eab672d5:


    "All of my suffering is nothing more than a test. {w}One that's only granted to those who hold the angel above all else in their hearts."


translate English day9_gr_a7e3b33b:


    "Thank you, God. Thank you for the gift of life."


translate English day9_gr_fa55d0af:


    "The rise and fall of my stomach in time with my breathing is barely perceptible, and cold sweat runs down my hot body."


translate English day9_gr_004dbb08:


    et "I..."


translate English day9_gr_0194dc6d:


    my_q2 "[na2]...?"


translate English day9_gr_3d7039a6:


    my_q "Hey... You don't look good at all. You should head back and get some..."


translate English day9_gr_d84bac32:


    pl "Huh? {w}What the... Who... who are you?"


translate English day9_gr_0583c86c:


    nar "I step back from her. {w}Looking around, I have no idea where I am. Everything feels weird."


translate English day9_gr_c912d416:


    pl "What the hell? This can't be happening... Where's the angel?"


translate English day9_gr_f1b6afda:


    my_q "[na2], what's wrong? {w}You're scaring me..."


translate English day9_gr_c8330e97:


    pl "D-Don't come any closer!!!"


translate English day9_gr_0db6ed20:


    nar "Goose bumps break out all over my skin. {w}She's a monster pretending to be an innocent soul, wearing some woman's skin. A horrific, hostile world sprawls out before me."


translate English day9_gr_f252f3da:


    pl "Ah... Aaaah!!!" with sshake


translate English day9_gr_45119201:



    nvl clear
    et "\n Letting out a hoarse scream, I begin to run, my feet pounding against the slippery floor."


translate English day9_gr_32dc0e29:



    nvl clear
    "\n My mind still manages to remember the way back home despite the sick and twisted landscape. {w}All I can do is pray the door is unlocked, even if this room belongs to someone else."


translate English day9_gr_0f79e1db:


    et "My palm is so sweaty that I can't get a good grip. My body's still trembling. {w}I manage to calm down and after a few deep breaths to steady myself, I open the door. And then immediately shut it."


translate English day9_gr_426fcf2f:



    nvl clear
    "\n I shudder to think what might happen if someone, or rather something, stepped inside after me."


translate English day9_gr_bff5b17b:


    "Just when I thought I'd finally woken up, I find myself back inside that disgusting nightmare!!!" with sshake


translate English day9_gr_8872c3f8:


    "I throw myself into bed, bury my face in my pillow, and scream. {w}Why? Why is this suddenly happening to me? She was supposed to be the angel who heard my confession!"


translate English day9_gr_66c2e3fc:


    "No one could have held me accountable for anything as long as the angel herself didn't accuse me of any crime, and my soul would have remained spotlessly pure. I remain level-headed from within the depths of my despair. {w}The only difference between yesterday and today are those pills Grette gave me."


translate English day9_gr_d09b28c5:


    et "Because I took medicine that denies her existence, despite the fact that the angel is not a hallucination of any kind. She defiled my soul. She abandoned me."


translate English day9_gr_c9802ae9:



    nvl clear
    "\n A wave of crushing hopelessness washes over me at the realization. {w}The angel is no longer by my side. {w}All for the stupid mistake of wanting another woman to like me!" with sshake


translate English day9_gr_9ae5445f:


    "I throw the rest of the pills in the trash. {w}The sin I had committed that day remains immortalized in that split-second snapshot of her dirty and degraded body tucked away in my dresser drawer. My sin remains under my control."


translate English day9_gr_202e346e:


    et "I roll over and offer up a prayer from the darkness beneath my blankets. {w}I can't seem to stop shivering, though it has nothing to do with being cold."


translate English day9_gr_76b2fe88_5:


    nvl clear


translate English day10_gr_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day10_gr_775d11ac:


    "\n I'm unable to sleep at all. Though I get the feeling I'd been lost in thought all night, deep in prayer."


translate English day10_gr_26a5ea31:


    "When I close my tired eyes, I can hear the sound of her wings coming from my pillow. {w}But when I open them again, I'm alone, and the cycle repeats itself endlessly."


translate English day10_gr_6c476787:


    "The sun has been up the entire time I've lain here in bed, trapped in this state of existence."


translate English day10_gr_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day10_gr_fa1ad227:


    "\n I close my eyes, trying to shut out my headache, which is when I hear a faint noise coming from outside my door. Like a short, sharp knock. {w}He's back, despite what happened yesterday."


translate English day10_gr_fe18afcf:


    "I try to simply ignore him at first. But the harder I try to force myself to sleep, the louder his voice gets, until eventually my anger overcomes my exhaustion."


translate English day10_gr_2da1e188:


    et "I get out of bed and head to the door, but the moment my hand reaches for the knob, the sound stops, almost as if it had never existed."


translate English day10_gr_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day10_gr_a756469a:


    "\n No one's there."


translate English day10_gr_8c9caec4:


    "What in the hell is going on? {w}I immediately knock on the door next to mine."


translate English day10_gr_5a44cec8:


    et "There's no answer. He must have fled as soon as he heard my footsteps approaching."


translate English day10_gr_14cc1d0c:



    nvl clear
    "\n I hear a loud bang from beside me, and I whirl around to face my now closed door, a chill racing down my spine. {w}Come to think of it, I was in such a hurry that I didn't take the time to close it properly."


translate English day10_gr_d369d04a:


    "The dormitory feels almost abnormally quiet. It might be early, but there still should be at least a few folks getting ready for the day ahead."


translate English day10_gr_d37315c9:


    "What if there's someone inside...? The prospect alone is terrifying enough that I can't bring myself to open the door. {w}I hurry into the main hallway as quickly and quietly as possible. Once I'm safely out of the dorms, I begin running without looking back."


translate English day10_gr_0632c53d:


    et "There are a few people in the temple, like usual. I'm glad I ended up not changing out of my clothes after I got back the night before. {w}If I had, I would currently be wandering the temple hallways in my pajamas."


translate English day10_gr_0a8df6ee:


    nar "The moment I step inside the Cleanup Department's office, practically everyone there turns to look at me. The drab and quiet atmosphere in the room is emphasized by an overwhelming sense of desolation."


translate English day10_gr_6c289b7d:


    hk "Brother?"


translate English day10_gr_086ad388:


    nar "I look around as I try to take in the bizarre scene before me, and yet nothing seems any different from how it usually is."


translate English day10_gr_e29835ff:


    nar "The bishop speaks to me as I stand frozen by the door."


translate English day10_gr_771c14e6:


    hk "Please take a seat."


translate English day10_gr_0c2891aa:


    nar "Her elegant voice lacks even a hint of agitation, and I nod in response. I make my way to my seat with my head lowered, only my eyes moving this way and that."


translate English day10_gr_fe4f55e9:


    nar "I see several pairs of legs underneath the row of desks."


translate English day10_gr_d3e51ab2:


    nar "A strong and cold wind blows through the crack in the window. It's hard to believe no one's fixed that yet."


translate English day10_gr_fbe89a46:


    hk "That's enough for today. Be sure to love one another, as God loves you."


translate English day10_gr_197049a4:


    nar "The desolation of the room is broken by her goodbye and the air is quickly filled with commotion. {w}I get up and hurry to stop him before he can leave."


translate English day10_gr_7c26b25c:


    pl "Hey, you!" with sshake


translate English day10_gr_f4b81df7:


    nar "The bishop, who's standing next to him, also turns to face me. {w}He seems surprised when I grab his arm, though his expression softens when he realizes who it is."


translate English day10_gr_9ee6faff:


    nar "Almost as if he knew this would happen."


translate English day10_gr_7079dd59:


    sc "What?"


translate English day10_gr_53532202:


    pl "What was your freaking deal this morning? I told you before to mind your own damn business!!!"


translate English day10_gr_15e5dcb2:


    nar "He blinks at me, his eyes dull with incomprehension, and then he suddenly nods as if my words triggered some kind of memory."


translate English day10_gr_7405082a:


    sc "Oh, right. {w}Well? So what? You're here, aren't you?"


translate English day10_gr_aa4ec619:


    pl "I'm s-sorry? {w}Don't f-fucking play games with me...!" with sshake


translate English day10_gr_282c096d:


    nar "I let go of his arm and instead grab him by the front of his shirt. Yet he remains seemingly unfazed as he looks back at me."


translate English day10_gr_ee1dc36c:


