    gr "I'm sorry I had to leave so abruptly yesterday."


translate English day10_gr_1e5f906b:


    gr "There was an emergency I had to deal with, and it took me completely by surprise..."


translate English day10_gr_de8aa605:


    pl "As a doctor, are you allowed to give certain patients preferential treatment?"


translate English day10_gr_58858be8:


    gr "I do what I can to treat all my patients equally."


translate English day10_gr_4cacae85:


    pl "But you left me there."


translate English day10_gr_330da748:


    gr "Because I was needed elsewhere!"


translate English day10_gr_d23409ff:


    pl "But I always need you, Doc."


translate English day10_gr_566cf9af:


    gr "Sorry... I'm sorry, [na2]. It won't happen again."


translate English day10_gr_eb1e660c_8:


    pl "..."


translate English day10_gr_d31e17bd:


    pl "What's your thoughts on sin, Doc?"


translate English day10_gr_e2bcfac3:


    gr "Huh?"


translate English day10_gr_b55f2845:


    pl "If a sinner doesn't repent, will their immoral soul be infected by Pestis, which was sent down to earth by God?"


translate English day10_gr_98acb172:


    gr "Pestis isn't some kind of mythical damnation inflicted on sinful people. It can happen to anyone."


translate English day10_gr_7abd7c38:


    pl "Why do virtuous people get infected by Pestis?"


translate English day10_gr_50af5026:


    gr "Because Pestis is nothing more than an unfortunate accident. Even if someone who committed a sin is infected by Pestis and dies, at the end of the day, it had nothing to do with their actions. They were just unlucky."


translate English day10_gr_2f8a6b90:


    pl "What if the assailant was originally a victim? {w}Do they still need to be punished?"


translate English day10_gr_5c479955:


    gr "No matter what sad circumstances may have led to a crime, all wrongdoers must be punished for their actions."


translate English day10_gr_94535434:


    gr "That's not illogical or frustrating, but simply how life works."


translate English day10_gr_4ea23adc:


    pl "How do you weed out the souls that have become impure?"


translate English day10_gr_f4ecf554:


    pl "You're saying that we have to live life constantly being scrutinized by the people around us and with the fear that Pestis might infect us at any moment, no matter what we do?!"


translate English day10_gr_9f3ec09a:


    gr "As long as our souls are graced by God then no one has the right to call them impure."


translate English day10_gr_dea92e6c:


    gr "The Lord's grace is always visible on our bodies through the visible sign of the stigmata."


translate English day10_gr_f218222d:


    pl "But..."


translate English day10_gr_dbfd96f2:


    gr "[na2]! {w}Try and calm down. I'll get you a nice cup of hot tea..." with sshake


translate English day10_gr_eb1e660c_9:


    pl "..."


translate English day10_gr_402b7a8b:


    nar "She walks over to where the cups are. I hear the sound of water being boiled."


translate English day10_gr_10a070a3:


    nar "If we're destined to sin, then why doesn't Heaven rain down punishment on our souls before we have the opportunity to do so?"


translate English day10_gr_6dbad34d:


    nar "Is it because your soul doesn't become impure until you actually commit the sin in question?"


translate English day10_gr_42328845:


    nar "If that's true, then does one soul only become corrupt once they've completed whatever task they were destined to do?"


translate English day10_gr_0798ceb2:


    nar "Or is it because of something else?"


translate English day10_gr_e6232e51:


    nar "If so, is that considered an opportunity? {w}Pestis? {w}Medicine?"


translate English day10_gr_eb1e660c_10:


    pl "..."


translate English day10_gr_e2a3ecde:


    nar "I unwrap half my bandages. My stigmata is still on my arm. {w}And it's presence means that God's grace still flows through me, according to the doctor."


translate English day10_gr_9a2d0339:


    nar "If the path I chose to follow is corrupt then that's basically the same as saying my sanctity has been sullied."


translate English day10_gr_996fe273:


    nar "The grace I was born with would stop flowing through me, causing my body itself to rot from the inside out. {w}And when that happens, then other people will realize how impure my soul has become."


translate English day10_gr_7ddf5fa3:


    nar "I take out the saw and rip off the rest of the bandages. My arm has already begun to rot."


translate English day10_gr_32378674:


    nar "Viscous pus oozes out from under my skin around my scars and maggots wriggle in and out of the gaping wound. My soul is... {w}No, there's still time."


translate English day10_gr_8e01d181:


    nar "I jam the saw into my flesh. I move the jagged blade back and forth as I cut off my hand at the wrist."


translate English day10_gr_44734da0:


    nar "My white, scuffed skin peels back, and blood oozes out from beneath. {w}Bright, vivid, red blood."


translate English day10_gr_05c8ec14:


    nar "It's not rotten after all, meaning my soul is still pure."


translate English day10_gr_defc963d:


    nar "As long as I can scrape out all the rotten parts, I can make my soul new again. {w}I yank the saw back and forth as I struggle to cut off my decomposing flesh."


translate English day10_gr_a791b42a:


    nar "My wrist feels hot, and yet the blade embedded into my skin feels so cold."


translate English day10_gr_761ea9d6:


    gr "[na2]! Stop!!!" with sshake


translate English day10_gr_ac0b8a99:


    nar "The moment I hear her panicked voice, I feel her grab my arm but I'm hellbent on chopping off as much corrupted flesh as I can."


translate English day10_gr_50b03d0f:


    nar "The saw drops from my hand with a loud clunk as it hits the floor. {w}I scramble to grab the saw but Grette kicks it away before I can."


translate English day10_gr_83c0a156:


    nar "It flies across the floor in a spinning motion, leaving a trail of blood behind it. I can feel my pulse pounding in my hot arm."


translate English day10_gr_f9ebb33f:


    nar "Just a little more! I just need to get rid of a little more flesh!" with sshake


translate English day10_gr_49ba739d:


    nar "I claw at my arm, scratching desperately at my mangled skin."


translate English day10_gr_2d462712:


    nar "If I crush my putrid skin, rip off the blood clots, and dig out the maggots, there still might be something salvageable underneath..."


translate English day10_gr_66d5f288:


    gr "Stop! I'm begging you to stop...!"


translate English day10_gr_4fa797fe:


    nar "Her hands grab mine, holding them as if in prayer. Sweat drips down her chin."


translate English day10_gr_0b6c59b4:


    nar "Pain suddenly flares up in my arm that was previously only tight and itchy, and I start crying most likely due to the discomfort. {w}I notice a chunk of pitch-black flesh underneath my white fingernail."


translate English day10_gr_016d49d6:


    pl "My sanctity is corrupt. My soul is impure..."


translate English day10_gr_616c6d02:


    gr "It's not corrupt! Take another look. You're hallucinating. {w}What you're seeing isn't real!"


translate English day10_gr_4dfcd8ab:


    gr "You seek forgiveness, don't you, [na2]? {w}That's why you're acting this way, right?"


translate English day10_gr_fd8aa763:


    gr "You need to get a hold of yourself. Sin can only be forgiven if the person feels remorse for what they did. {w}Part of that includes accepting retribution."


translate English day10_gr_78079a04:


    pl "Who can both forgive me and punish me?!"


translate English day10_gr_1b59583d:


    gr "I can... I know your sins better than anyone, so I am fully capable of forgiving you. {w}Right? So, please, just stop..."


translate English day10_gr_48513df1:


    pl "Don't try and make it sound that easy! You're always trying to trick me like that! I'm not a patient you can cure!"


translate English day10_gr_a51fb3ca:


    gr "You are my patient, so when will you see that I'm not here to harm you? {w}All I want to do is help you!"


translate English day10_gr_dd241b0a:


    pl "The only person you want to help is yourself. {w}Forgiveness? You just want to bury this entire incident as deep as possible."


translate English day10_gr_3e2ccd6b:


    gr "This kind of behavior is only further proof of your unstable mind."


translate English day10_gr_c554ec62:


    gr "You say you don't want to accept the burden of your sins and you don't want to trust anyone. All you do is push others away."


translate English day10_gr_f5a527e1:


    gr "But are you really okay with being alone? {w}You know that means all of your friends vanish as well, right?"


translate English day10_gr_68e487b6:


    pl "What fucking friends are you referring to? {w}I'm already all alone. I'm a sinner on the verge of death, and everyone's trying to kill me."


translate English day10_gr_65f600e2:


    pl "You talk about punishing me! {w}As if you were some kind of God. I guess Pestis infected your soul, too, huh?"


translate English day10_gr_c0471ffe:


    pl "You spend your life helping others, and God gave you a defective body in return!"


translate English day10_gr_a1583445:


    gr "God made me this way for a reason."


translate English day10_gr_40071a91:


    gr "The gift of life may not flow through my veins, but that only means I can devote myself to taking care of other children,"


translate English day10_gr_e3a0c4c3:


    gr "and I don't have to worry about generational trauma. Have you ever thought of it that way? {w}You have to look on the bright side!"


translate English day10_gr_81fb6a47:


    pl "The bright side? Just sounds like self-deceptive rationalization to me. {w}Though I envy your optimism."


translate English day10_gr_cdc714b6:


    gr "Why do you keep denying your own illness, [na2]? Why?"


translate English day10_gr_ea82c96d:


    pl "What do you mean, why? It should be obvious. I don't want to be your patient."


translate English day10_gr_81535416:


    gr "But why?"


translate English day10_gr_0dd61846:


    pl "Because I like you! You've known for a while now, so why act like it's a mystery?!" with sshake


translate English day10_gr_adb22f35:


    pl "The love, care, and tenderness you feel obligated to show your patients... {w}I hate it more than anything! Understand?!"


translate English day10_gr_216f063f:


    gr "That's not... I mean everything I do. {w}I always try to be sincere with each and every one of my patients."


translate English day10_gr_1cfb28fd:


    pl "Because you have to?"


translate English day10_gr_12bb6eb0:


    gr "Exactly! {w}And is that so wrong? I'm your doctor! And you can always count on me to support you!"


translate English day10_gr_dc6b5b94:


    pl "What made you even consider marrying that man? Because there was someone like me hanging around you, right?"


translate English day10_gr_2f9a98ca:


    pl "And you figured you could get him to leave you alone if you belonged to someone else? {w}Something like that?"


translate English day10_gr_c337ede0:


    gr "You talk about people like they're objects..."


translate English day10_gr_0087da59:


    pl "You're the one who called yourself a doctor a moment ago. {w}To tell you the truth, I've never felt the title meant anything special."


translate English day10_gr_d9a8dd60:


    pl "But clearly, you feel differently."


translate English day10_gr_0932cb95:


    pl "What exactly does it mean to you, and why does it matter so much? {w}When are you not a doctor? When you're with him?"


translate English day10_gr_3fcd88b0:


    gr "Being stubborn won't change the facts. {w}I'm Gregor Cornish's wife! Grette Cornish!"


translate English day10_gr_ae43232b:


    gr "And no matter what anyone says, we share the same last name! You're overthinking things and are a mess of emotions right now."


translate English day10_gr_d3891624:


    pl "Please. Just give me a chance..."


translate English day10_gr_32747c28:


    nar "I reach out toward her with my bloody arm."


translate English day10_gr_5b91ce30:


    nar "She simply stares at my hand as it slowly draws closer before taking a step backwards."


translate English day10_gr_597bf928:


    gr "No..."


translate English day10_gr_42f11f47:


    pl "Come on. You're always talking about helping me, so how can you say no to the only thing I really want?"


translate English day10_gr_477e3afc:


    pl "Why give me hope when you were never planning on doing anything but lead me on?! I would have preferred if you never tried to help me at all!"


translate English day10_gr_18b57af0:


    gr "Not help you? {w}When I find someone that needs help, I can't just stand by and do nothing. {w}I'm always thinking up ways to make them feel better,"


translate English day10_gr_57af940a:


    gr "praying night and day for their happiness... willing to help in any way I can whenever they come to me with their problems,"


translate English day10_gr_5876cb59:


    gr "and I make sure I'm up to date with the latest in medical advancements and psychiatric care so I can be the best doctor to my patients...!"


translate English day10_gr_ffc4034d:


    pl "Your mind's somewhere else."


translate English day10_gr_eab85036:


    gr "What are you talking about? {w}Are you saying I'm thinking about another patient when you're right in front of me, [na2]?"


translate English day10_gr_0a09b5d2:


    pl "There's just something slightly off. {w}You've seemed exhausted for a few days, but you're especially out of it today."


translate English day10_gr_cb7d7db7:


    gr "Sigh... Not this again..."


translate English day10_gr_8304e0ba:


    pl "I met with my bishop today, and she asked if I was taking my medicine."


translate English day10_gr_d525221f:


    pl "What the hell did you give me? You're really trying to turn me into a psychopath, huh?"


translate English day10_gr_6726974b:


    gr "That medicine is supposed to make you feel better, not worse."


translate English day10_gr_f3ea0f4b:


    gr "I had to get permission from the head of your department since it can make you tired, which might in turn affect your work performance."


translate English day10_gr_a81d3113:


    gr "Though from the state you're currently in, I can tell you haven't been taking the medicine. {w}I should have been more clear from the start..."


translate English day10_gr_8b6a25a8:


    gr "You need therapy."


translate English day10_gr_46238c59:


    pl "You're the one who needs therapy! {w}Take what just happened. All I said was your mind's somewhere else. You're the one who brought up other patients."


translate English day10_gr_1c06485b:


    pl "I know how hard your job is, but don't you think you're overworking yourself?"


translate English day10_gr_f1192012:


    pl "You're openly irritated, giving half-assed therapy sessions, pushing your own agenda on your patients, sobbing at the drop of a hat... You weren't always like this."


translate English day10_gr_3d57b93c:


    gr "And whose fault do you think that is?!" with sshake


translate English day10_gr_16a63a1b:


    gr "Sigh... Uh... Oh, god... No, I have to calm down...!" with sshake


translate English day10_gr_6c358a7a:


    pl "What happened yesterday? {w}Talk to me about it, Grette. Just like before."


translate English day10_gr_f517f968:


    nar "She closes the binder full of documents without responding. The sharp sound of it shutting cuts through the deepening silence."


translate English day10_gr_568236ce:


    gr "I'm sorry, [na2]. I'm quite tired, so I'll be leaving earlier than usual."


translate English day10_gr_49c778e6:


    nar "The light goes out with a soft click."


translate English day10_gr_b315a417:


    nar "A somber gloominess hangs in the air in front of me, and I hurriedly get to my feet as she leaves the infirmary."


translate English day10_gr_757c4076:


    pl "Wait! You're leaving?! {w}Just like that?!" with sshake


translate English day10_gr_f92ddc72:


    nar "She slowly raises her head. The Grette I see in the darkness seems like a complete stranger."


translate English day10_gr_c7d0cae6:


    nar "She slowly closes her eyes, her tears glistening in the darkness. {w}The moment she opens them again, she frowns."


translate English day10_gr_b7f3ddef:


    gr "You reek of cigarettes."


translate English day10_gr_b5a42682:


    nar "Then she walks past me on her way out."


translate English day10_gr_a496db9c:


    nar "When I saw the frown on her face, I thought for a moment she was actually about to get angry at me."


translate English day10_gr_1a2dbd2b:


    nar "I thought she might hit my back or shoulders, or at the very least give me a look of disapproval."


translate English day10_gr_6324045f:


    nar "What kind of outcome am I hoping to get from this situation? {w}I'm the one fucking it all up."


translate English day10_gr_de1b3246:


    nar "She's right. I used up all my chances and I shoved all of my friends away."


translate English day10_gr_186e9480:


    nar "No. {w}I did it for the angel, and for myself. I had no choice. {w}Even if there had been another way to get the same results, it's too late now..."


translate English day10_gr_72eb8873:



    nvl clear
    "\n There are no marks left on the door. The door that had scared me shitless this morning opened easily, and there was no one inside. Of course."


translate English day10_gr_3ac0f568:


    et "And yet I still don't feel at ease. The familiar room and all the stuff inside suddenly looks unfamiliar and foreign. {w}I end up sitting in the corner of my room on the floor instead of on my bed."


translate English day10_gr_76b2fe88_4:


    nvl clear


translate English day10_gr_5c426463:


    "\n In that silence, I remember my mother. {w}Whenever I got into trouble, the other adults would always yell at me with expressions of annoyance. Afterwards, as if part of some standard procedure, they'd get this overbearing look in their eyes, as if able to see into my soul... {w}And while spouting a bunch of nonsense bullshit, they'd invariably bring up my mom."


translate English day10_gr_9b16b37b:


    et "I'd been raised from birth by the adults in my village, and despite never knowing my mom's name or even hearing her voice, I carried the debt of life she bestowed on me, seemingly branded into my very soul."


translate English day10_gr_52c974fb:



    nvl clear
    "\n It pissed me off. I was never unhappy about the absence of my parents, nor was I frustrated or disappointed, and yet I held onto my own unique hopes and dreams. The dream that someone might love me and only me, and not because they feel obligated to do so for the sake of the community and a need to keep the peace."


translate English day10_gr_7f1495e9:


    "Which is what led to that fateful day when I threw a tantrum and went to find my mom. She was gorgeous. {w}She was living happily with a bright smile on her face and a cheerfulness in her voice revealing her youth."


translate English day10_gr_e9095050:


    et "I'd never seen her before, this woman who was always surrounded by people and who bore no resemblance to me. I ended up running away from home, as far as I could go, before throwing up. I hadn't even been able to speak to her. I knew she didn't need me in her life, that I would only get in the way."


translate English day10_gr_aa803cdf:



    nvl clear
    "\n I never saw her again after that. {w}Or my dad, either. {w}Afraid that I might accidentally bump into them, I lived my life making a point to avoid them at all costs. By the time I became an adult, I had forgotten all about them."


translate English day10_gr_7a16ee63:


    "A memory I'd long since forgotten suddenly springs to mind."


translate English day10_gr_28012c29:


    "Perhaps my recollection is proof that it's significant and more than a mere memory. {w}I've managed to recreate my own birth in a way."


translate English day10_gr_049af3d0:


    et "It's proof that I've crossed the line, that I was once human."


translate English day10_gr_76b2fe88_5:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_aaf4c8bc:



    nvl clear
    "\n When I fall asleep, I dream about my mom who I don't remember."


translate English day11_gr_9bde02f8:


    "It's a simple dream. {w}Fragmented and easily forgotten upon waking."


translate English day11_gr_cf721d39:


    "I walked with her, hand in hand, through the fields outside my hometown as the bright sun rose in the sky. {w}I caught the pleasant scent of grains of rice from the wind and ran from the sight of a grasshopper who was bigger than my knuckle."


translate English day11_gr_f37b93f5:


    et "It was then that I noticed she was paler than how I remembered my mom to be, and her hair was longer, which is when I snapped awake."


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_ba84d154:


    et "\n The sky outside my window is blue, so I probably didn't sleep very long. {w}My body feels light."


translate English day11_gr_b3e690a3:


    nar "The world outside the temple walls is shrouded in white fog, hiding it from view."


translate English day11_gr_3f0af594:


    nar "The outlines of everything are blurred, as if I'm still in a dream, and the air feels cold against my skin."


translate English day11_gr_0871f305:


    nar "It's been a while since I arrived at the department office this early."


translate English day11_gr_4ec1e830:


    nar "It's not long before the other priests arrive and their boring morning meeting begins. I remain slumped over my desk the entire time, not speaking to anyone."


translate English day11_gr_ab8e7553:


    nar "No one talks to me unless I speak to them first. {w}Their constant side-eyes are painfully pathetic."


translate English day11_gr_2a965f5a:


    ex1 "Look, hypothetically speaking..."


translate English day11_gr_263831f2:


    nar "This morning, shortly after waking up, I very carefully turned a photo on my desk the other way around. {w}There was a reason behind doing so."


translate English day11_gr_2584d223:


    nar "The reason why my emotions and thoughts are such a mess is because of the sin created by and contained within that one photo."


translate English day11_gr_600f1185:


    ex1 "If you could fuck anyone in the temple... Who would it be?"


translate English day11_gr_6aa842c0:


    nar "When I hear the sound of a familiar name, I get up from my seat."


translate English day11_gr_f2d8c0e1:


    nar "Their disgusting voices immediately die down, and they freeze in place, trying to act inconspicuous."


translate English day11_gr_f0e86ab6:


    nar "I slowly approach them. {w}I don't think I've ever looked them in the face before, but they're all about the same height as I am."


translate English day11_gr_590c9747:


    pl "Why do you wanna fuck Dr. Grette?"


translate English day11_gr_7ba879f2:


    ex1 "What's your problem? Don't invite yourself into private conversations. You're so weird..."


translate English day11_gr_2788dfd4:


    pl "I don't think it's that weird."


translate English day11_gr_a4a93290:


    ex1 "Huh?"


translate English day11_gr_df07b810:


    nar "Instead of responding, I take a photo from the small pile I'm holding behind my back."


translate English day11_gr_5c829a65:


    nar "Those losers who can only grimly grumble about their impossible dreams look at me in shock."


translate English day11_gr_c4007c6d:


    ex1 "Is that...?"


translate English day11_gr_e28d9e5b:


    nar "Everyone's left speechless. {w}No one could have ever imagined it, because until this moment, I was the only one who'd seen the doctor like that."


translate English day11_gr_1f29620a:


    nar "I grab the arm of one of the guys in the pack as he takes a step back and shove the photo into his hand. {w}It's trembling faintly."


translate English day11_gr_22e3b916:


    nar "I need a gossipy guy like him to spread the good word for me. So everyone knows exactly who she belongs to."


translate English day11_gr_951c9161:


    nar "Let it be known to all so that no one dares laugh at me that way again."


translate English day11_gr_1a5205ba:


    nar "Make it so that she'll never be able to look anyone in the face again, that she'll never feel proud of herself. {w}Make it so she'll regret ever messing with me,"


translate English day11_gr_b2e4c2a5:


    nar "and every single word she's ever said to another human being... {w}Make it so that the only person she can remember is me..."


translate English day11_gr_8771e71e:


    nar "I hear a sharp, rustling sound from within my fist. {w}I accidentally used a bit too much force."


translate English day11_gr_985a6a58:


    nar "I stand in front of these assholes who can only barely read the room and try to think of something to say, but eventually I give up and leave without saying anything."


translate English day11_gr_99404ed7:


    nar "Without any paperwork or tools, my body really does feel light."


translate English day11_gr_84fe797c:



    nvl clear
    "\n I remember the day I headed to the infirmary in order to share a funny story with the doctor."


translate English day11_gr_3805c50b:


    "To tell you the truth, I don't really remember what the story was even about. It was just my way of shaking my depressive slump. {w}That or simply an excuse to talk to the doctor whenever possible."


translate English day11_gr_3c83b89c:


    "I really liked that place. It was the only bright spot in this cold, unfamiliar temple, with warmth and light."


translate English day11_gr_3c9eebff:


    et "A place specially designed for the priests where they could relax from the everyday stress and feelings of disgust towards the filth they deal with on the job that breaks their spirit. A place where all they have to worry about is sipping tea and eating snacks while engaging in friendly conversation..."


translate English day11_gr_500af1ab:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"What you youngsters need more than anything is someone more experienced you can trust.\""


translate English day11_gr_e17e7c43:


    et "I remember sitting there. {w}Dr. Grette was right in front of me, looking directly into my eyes with both of her own, which were sparkling with delight as she laughed. There was no crease between her eyebrows, no frown of worry, and she wasn't squinting as if trying to avoid talking with me."


translate English day11_gr_d9b50b8a:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Don't ever forget that there are always folks around who will help you if you ever need it.\""


translate English day11_gr_6f9ac281:


    "In her eyes, I'd been nothing more than a child who needed protection right from the very start, and I hated that fact. {w}I wanted to reject her obligatory kindness and affection... {w}Wait, why do I feel that way again?"


translate English day11_gr_cf9de34f:


    "Probably because I wanted to be her one and only. {w}I wanted a relationship with her where she would listen to me talk tirelessly until she came to know me as well as I had come to know her."


translate English day11_gr_815d3f2d:


    "Her kindness wasn't mine alone, but the more I learned about her, the more I needed it. {w}Which is exactly what pisses me off."


translate English day11_gr_cff10e36:


    et "Jealousy and envy, the most fundamental of emotions, have grown like cancerous tumors inside of my head."


translate English day11_gr_7ad3c90b:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"When you see someone struggle that hard, doesn't it make you want to cheer them on all the more?\""


translate English day11_gr_70d1bd98:


    et "Why couldn't it be?"


translate English day11_gr_380cc680:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Heh! I promise.\""


translate English day11_gr_66d2ca2e:


    "Am I really not good enough?"


translate English day11_gr_82dffb1a:


    "I can't go back to the way things once were anyways. {w}You made me do it. Why did you have to stick your nose where it didn't belong under the pretext of helping me? {w}Why did you keep making impossible promises?!"


translate English day11_gr_a8d375d8:


    et "Why were you such a freaking blabbermouth? Why did you always seem so happy to see me whenever I opened the door? {w}Why... Why...?"


translate English day11_gr_46759931:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"You really trust us that much, [na2]? {w}You know we're always here whenever you need us. You're putting so much effort into your work, and we want to support you as best we can.\""


translate English day11_gr_b6d4d699:


    et "\"You're always welcome to come back, whenever you want. {w}We can be the family that you never had.\""


translate English day11_gr_f88ee0d7:


    nar "My pace gradually quickens and before long, I break into a run."


translate English day11_gr_f9c43dc7:


    nar "I run down the hall, pushing past all the noisy people. {w}I race through the pure-white hospital ward, looking inside every room I can find."


translate English day11_gr_e596feec:


    nar "My lungs feel like they're shriveling up."


translate English day11_gr_e1430e73:


    nar "From time to time, I hear someone try to speak to me, but I can't make out their words."


translate English day11_gr_5f9b5cc2:


    nar "More and more people are gathering around me, probably due to the commotion I'm causing within the ward. {w}She's one of them."


translate English day11_gr_472612a4:


    nar "The hand that clamps down on me almost violently is cold and slim."


translate English day11_gr_af96b849:


    gr "What's wrong?"


translate English day11_gr_a109ca15:


    pl "I see the angel in my dreams every night, Doc. I thought it was a nightmare at first, but I was wrong. {w}The angel in my dreams is actually a girl I know very well." with sshake


translate English day11_gr_f5693773:


    pl "She's someone you know as well, Doc. I don't have the power to disobey her wishes or commands. She sleeps with me in my dreams and cuts off my filthy arm. "


translate English day11_gr_1aa694b4:


    pl "She tries to bring me to where she is..."


translate English day11_gr_c546364a:


    pl "It's not a dream anymore, it's real. She's not in the dream anymore. She's here in the real world. "


translate English day11_gr_eed7042b:


    pl "It happened a while ago. When I call her an angel, I don't mean it as a metaphor. She has wings. "


translate English day11_gr_c7c8c405:


    pl "She glows with a bright light and only I can see her! No one else can! She... she can punish me for my sins. "


translate English day11_gr_df4fa7bb:


    pl "I tell her of my sins every time I commit one. She's listened to all of my confessions, and because of that, my soul has been saved. "


translate English day11_gr_38bf880e:


    pl "But the angel hasn't appeared for a while now. Not since I started taking the medicine you gave me. "


translate English day11_gr_f69629e5:


    pl "She knows my soul is impure, and she doesn't want to save me any longer. What do I do, Doc? "


translate English day11_gr_bf9fd77b:


    pl "What the hell am I supposed to do?! I...!"


translate English day11_gr_e118093e:


    gr "Wait... I get it. {w}I understand everything, so just calm down for now." with sshake


translate English day11_gr_4a59703a:


    pl "You'll listen to me?"


translate English day11_gr_659b4dc4:


    gr "...! {w}O-Of course I will."


translate English day11_gr_785e0914:


    gr "You know you can tell me anything you need to get off your chest, [na2]. {w}That's my job, to listen to you..."


translate English day11_gr_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day11_gr_92a7512c:


    gr "I just... I have to finish up some things here first, so can you go on ahead and wait for me in the infirmary? {w}I'll be right there, I promise."


translate English day11_gr_254c18ea:


    gr "I should be done within ten minutes... {w}Okay?"


translate English day11_gr_c9caa47e:


    nar "I nod my head in agreement."


translate English day11_gr_9b07b6d9:


    nar "That alone is enough to bring a smile of joy to her lips, seemingly out of place against the backdrop of her pale complexion. She hurries on her way, glancing back at me several times."


translate English day11_gr_d06c2236:


    nar "The strength finally drains from my body. {w}I can talk to her while looking her in the face again."


translate English day11_gr_e7188113:


    nar "Though the reason I end up sneaking along behind her is because I spot Claire running up to her from the opposite direction."


translate English day11_gr_0b0ecc81:


    cr "Are you sure you're okay, Dr. Grette? {w}That guy is... not well."


translate English day11_gr_3a29e251:


    gr "I appreciate your concern, Claire."


translate English day11_gr_73809534:


    gr "But I finally have a chance with him. {w}I can't let it go without trying again."


translate English day11_gr_d0ebb36e:


    cr "But..."


translate English day11_gr_088f029d:


    gr "I'll be fine... {w}I have a plan in place."


translate English day11_gr_6e7e2d7d:


    nar "The doctor seems pleased, and I notice she's holding something in her hand."


translate English day11_gr_2e44e7a7:


    nar "It's a syringe. {w}Small enough that it can easily fit in her pocket. She's filling it with a clear liquid."


translate English day11_gr_6738830f:


    nar "Even from distance, I can see the light sparkle off the sharp tip of the needle."


translate English day11_gr_989670f3:


    pl "..."


translate English day11_gr_c7481b3c:


    gr "I'm sorry for running late, [na2]. {w}You weren't here long, right?"


translate English day11_gr_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "..."


translate English day11_gr_bf8f0096:


    gr "Hrm... How about a glass of warm milk? {w}We got a new supply yesterday."


translate English day11_gr_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "..."


translate English day11_gr_c97ad6d5:


    gr "Yeah? That's great. {w}Okay. If you need anything else, just let me know."


translate English day11_gr_eb1e660c_3:


    pl "..."


translate English day11_gr_e295e047:


    gr "So, um... About what you were saying earlier... Can you tell me a little more about it?"


translate English day11_gr_7527dc38:


    pl "I told you everything already."


translate English day11_gr_8fc6af14:


    gr "You were talking so quickly... I'd like to hear it again, but slower this time."


translate English day11_gr_d711a534:


    pl "The angel... {w}She doesn't just exist in my head anymore. She's here in the real world. She was talking to me just the other day."


translate English day11_gr_8648af3b:


    gr "Yeah? I don't doubt you... {w}But if what you're saying is true, [na2], then she's not here anymore, right?"


translate English day11_gr_76c018b5:


    pl "It's clear you do doubt me."


translate English day11_gr_0aaab370:


    gr "I'm not trying to deny your belief, but if it's hurting you in some way, then I'll do what I can to stop it."


translate English day11_gr_282e22d7:


    pl "Because you're my doctor?"


translate English day11_gr_221e55e8:


    gr "Exactly."


translate English day11_gr_50e0b075:


    pl "Here we go again. {w}You're only helping me because you feel obligated to, because you feel it's your duty to figure out some kind of a solution."


translate English day11_gr_de72ca46:


    pl "If I end up becoming completely unhinged, it'll hurt your good name, right? In the end, it's still all about you, huh?"


translate English day11_gr_dc2191a2:


    gr "I sincerely want to help you, [na2]... {w}Please, think about it."


translate English day11_gr_131e8e03:


    gr "This may very well be our last chance... {w}Who do you think can help you if not me?"


translate English day11_gr_2cb98706:


    nar "Our last chance? Does she really see it that way?"


translate English day11_gr_ea3fc086:


    nar "Considering it's too late to go back at this point, whose chance is it exactly?"


translate English day11_gr_679ba7d3:


    pl "Why am I nothing more than a psycho to you, Doc?"


translate English day11_gr_6300a7d8:


    pl "I just wanted to be with you, for you to see me as a normal person and not just one of your patients."


translate English day11_gr_6fdff94c:


    pl "And yet you treat me like I'm sick in the head until the very end. {w}I wanted to be someone special in your life."


translate English day11_gr_7b111e53:


    pl "I never wanted to be someone you'd so easily forget just because we stopped talking or hadn't seen each other in a while."


translate English day11_gr_b3e71504:


    pl "Why was that impossible?"


translate English day11_gr_4dba65ea:


    gr "..."


translate English day11_gr_907bdcfa:


    pl "I know how much it means for you to try and be a better doctor than anyone else... {w}And I know you need me to be sick in order to advance your career."


translate English day11_gr_f4e52640:


    pl "That's why you cling to me, why you're always trying to talk to me... Don't think I don't get it."


translate English day11_gr_d0a28bb8:


    pl "But I've had enough... and is that really so wrong? {w}Did you ever once try to actually understand me?"


translate English day11_gr_fcf090ff:


    pl "Weren't you supposed to take care of me? You should have known what I was so worried about, right?"


translate English day11_gr_d9614bac:


    pl "So why didn't you ever take me seriously?"


translate English day11_gr_4dba65ea_1:


    gr "..."


translate English day11_gr_08ba0a5c:


    pl "It's just... if you were going to drop the ball halfway through, wouldn't it have been better to have not gotten involved at all?"


translate English day11_gr_5340285a:


    pl "Why did you intentionally mislead me by calling me family?"


translate English day11_gr_a2729f69:


    pl "I thought you accepted me for who I was, and I had high hopes that I'd finally found somewhere I belonged..."


translate English day11_gr_b38892d6:


    nar "I'd finally accepted the reality of the situation. {w}There was no point in questioning her guilt."


translate English day11_gr_eee83de2:


    nar "Persecuting someone for their morality or sense of righteousness is irresponsibly ridiculous."


translate English day11_gr_99addd38:


    nar "I'm no position to judge her anyways since I don't have to the right to dole out punishment."


translate English day11_gr_dfffa330:


    nar "The guilt is mine alone, and I'm the only one who can bear this sin."


translate English day11_gr_423bce54:


    nar "It's not long before the sinner hangs his head in shame as she stands there before me. {w}A cruel silence cloaks my blurred vision."


translate English day11_gr_9a1aa6da:


    gr "I don't understand..."


translate English day11_gr_5aef9d3c:


    gr "Why does it bother you so much when other people are kind to you? Why do you always complain to me and refuse to take the medicine I got specifically for you to feel better?"


translate English day11_gr_64752923:


    gr "How is it that two people can be so damn similar...?"


translate English day11_gr_2fff49e1:


    nar "Though the words she speaks are neither those of forgiveness nor punishment."


translate English day11_gr_88255d9c:



    nvl clear
    "\n I find myself feeling lucid."


translate English day11_gr_b5948f87:


    "I pick up my chair and throw it onto the desk. {w}Neat stacks of paperwork go flying everywhere and a typewriter along with a cute mug and a couple other miscellaneous objects fall to the ground." with sshake


translate English day11_gr_7c61cdfa:


    "And with that, whatever so-called last chance I might once have had vanishes completely. {w}This woman never knew the real me, and I've been well aware of that for a while now."


translate English day11_gr_f4cb10b1:


    et "The blood seems to drain from her face as she watches me, but I can't bring myself to meet her gaze with mine. {w}There's a fear in her eyes of someone who isn't me."


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_2:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_4b134fe4:


    "\n It's a good thing I got a hold of a weapon before coming here. The pair of scissors I'd so hastily grabbed had some random Health Department priest's name written on them. {w}The object wasn't important--I just needed something I could use to threaten her life with."


translate English day11_gr_78b7485b:


    "As she stumbles about in a frantic attempt at escape, I grab a hank of her hair. {w}Those long strands so perfectly resemble the type of hairstyle one might find on a mother character in a book."


translate English day11_gr_9a8186ff:


    et "She seems right at home wearing white aprons and serving warm tea to young children. Though she's currently being restrained by a hellish monster."


translate English day11_gr_4d90827e:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Haaah...\""


translate English day11_gr_c2145ed3:


    "I exhale before plunging the scissors into her neck. {w}That neck of hers, as white and slender as a willow branch, trembles. {w}Looking closer, I realize her entire body is trembling. Though I chalk it up to feeling cold and not out of fear."


translate English day11_gr_a317a63f:


    "Her small, thin lips are almost purple, as if she's freezing to death, and her thin, bare legs stretching out from beneath her sweater to her slipper-clad feet seem incredibly cold."


translate English day11_gr_859e645d:


    et "She remains silent, looking at me instead of the scissors sticking out of her neck. {w}Her gaze is a complex mix of emotions. There's equal parts fear, sadness, and anger, yet she's still struggling to maintain a facade of cool composure."


translate English day11_gr_0c09509f:



    nvl clear
    "\n Then she suddenly drops her gaze and reaches into her pocket. {w}For the syringe. {w}The plan she had in place to kill me."


translate English day11_gr_1ea78416:


    "\"Aah!\"" with sshake


translate English day11_gr_faf09b25:


    "I yank the scissors from her neck before cutting off the bundle of her hair I have gripped in my fist."


translate English day11_gr_c3d3b50d:


    et "Having chopped off the means with which I'd been holding her up, she immediately slumps to the ground. {w}I hold her severed braid in my hand. {w}It feels light."


translate English day11_gr_95313655:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"That look suits you better, Grette."


translate English day11_gr_6b5abf17:


    et "You look even more motherly than before!\""


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_3:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_4:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_de62c209:


    "\n She reaches up to the wound in her neck where she'd been stabbed and squeezes her eyes shut, as if only just now realizing what just happened. {w}Then, with a look of determination on her face, she gets to her feet and grabs my arm."


translate English day11_gr_35d02501:


    "Her grip isn't very strong, but I can't seem to break free. {w}As I desperately struggle to get loose, she brings out the syringe that she'd kept a tight hold of even after falling to the ground, not even bothering to look for a vein."


translate English day11_gr_50a6ff39:


    et "The situation is progressing through brute force alone. It's like she's dealing with criminal who clearly deserves to be punished or a violent animal who can't speak. {w}I can feel blood rising behind my eyelids. It's almost as if she's letting me know exactly how someone like me should be treated."


translate English day11_gr_6f973ea0:



    nvl clear
    "\n I manage to swing the arm she's holding onto as hard as possible into the nearby bookcase. {w}I assumed the force of the impact would make her let go, but I clearly underestimated her tenacity. {w}She doesn't let go, even while various medicine bottles crash around us."


translate English day11_gr_4f499eeb:


    "The cold needle finally slips into my wrist. Though instead of pain, a blood-curdling chill spreads through my entire body. {w}A scream like the dying howl of an animal rips from my throat, but it doesn't make any sense. {w}It sounds like someone else's voice, a complete stranger."


translate English day11_gr_e0834ca7:


    et "As she starts depressing the plunger, I reach for the bookcase before she can inject me with the full contents of the syringe. {w}I grab one of the bottles and bring it down onto her head."


translate English day11_gr_d618a065:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Aah... Aaaaah!!!\"" with sshake


translate English day11_gr_d758c6c4:


    "She immediately backs away while covering her face with both hands, convulsing as if having a seizure. {w}As her voice grows fainter, my vision shatters into a multitude of parts."


translate English day11_gr_463c5885:


    et "I'm barely clinging to consciousness as a pungent, acidic stench shoots through my nose and directly into my brain."


translate English day11_gr_93788f7d:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"I thought you were a doctor. You should be able to handle that much, right?\""


translate English day11_gr_3a5b74c1:


    "As my neck gets heavier, my gaze naturally lowers. {w}I notice a medicine jar on the desk and the shattered remains of another along with what appears to be a label. It probably has the name of the medication written on it, but I can't make it out."


translate English day11_gr_1c456ef9:


    "Hidden amongst those shards of glass is the syringe she'd been holding. {w}I reach out for it with one shaky hand, grabbing it before shoving it into her neck as she remains convulsing on the floor. Then I depress the plunger as hard as I can."


translate English day11_gr_de741868:


    et "To make sure I get the job done right. {w}The syringe is wet and the mystery liquid splatters everywhere, soaking my cheeks and fingertips."


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_5:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_aca64102:


    "\n A quiet, faint scream fades away. {w}Her arms slump lifelessly to the ground. Pale skin on her exposed face is peeled back to reveal a swollen, bright-red dermis. {w}The steady sound of my heartbeat sends scorching heat rushing through my cold body."


translate English day11_gr_884e0007:


    "I want her to be my woman, but I'm not sure in what sense of the word \"woman\" I want her."


translate English day11_gr_33e06ded:


    "And yet, somehow, I remain clinging to hope even here, at the very end of it all. I want to ask her directly. {w}What do you want me to be, Grette? What kind of person do you want me to be? {w}And what on earth were you thinking when you said the word \"family\"?"


translate English day11_gr_a7cf532e:


    et "\"Why...\""


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_6:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_5dab926f:


    "\n I hold the sleeping doctor in my arms. Wrapped in her warmth, I close my eyes, and my head gets progressively heavier. A peacefulness forcibly takes control of my consciousness."


translate English day11_gr_33e90ba4:


    "And I wonder why. {w}I feel the weight of her hand on the top of my head, stroking my hair gently. {w}It feels like a dream. Maybe it is."


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_7:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_086994eb:


    "\n Just then, someone's foot comes crashing against me, knocking me back down. {w}I roll away from Grette's body but before my mind has time to register the pain, someone grabs me by the front of my shirt." with sshake


translate English day11_gr_b4286601:


    et "I'm assaulted by painful blows to the bones and cartilage that make up the features of my face--from my jaw and my cheeks to my nose. It's sudden enough that I don't have time to catch my breath."


translate English day11_gr_673be979:


    nvl clear 


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_8:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_0b3e38f9:


    "\n \"You... fucking piece of shit...\""


translate English day11_gr_09bc5f77:


    "I hear a quiet yet furious voice right in front of me. {w}Only the man's face is clearly visible from out of the blurred landscape of my fragmented vision."


translate English day11_gr_73a1cf9e:


    "His eyes are wide open, displaying his black pupils which tremble as if he's struggling to suppress his rising emotions, though the sound of his harsh breathing makes his rage obvious."


translate English day11_gr_fc861698:


    "My subdued emotions well up once again inside me. I feel blood trickling from my nose to my upper lip, and the corner of my mouth curls up into a smirk."


translate English day11_gr_183255aa:


    et "I hadn't meant to provoke him, but my vision begins stuttering in and out again. {w}There's a high-pitched ringing in my ears, and the world spins crazily around me." with sshake


translate English day11_gr_d338e22e:



    nvl clear
    "\n \"Wait... {w}Stop! No! Don't hit him! {w}Stop hitting him!\"" with sshake


translate English day11_gr_d681acb4:


    "I hear the sound of a woman sobbing once again. Her desperate pleas seems completely out of place in this heated environment. {w}I'm not hallucinating, though. It's Grette, who's crying while clinging to the man's waist."


translate English day11_gr_f5ffa888:


    "She hasn't even bothered to wipe off her face which is covered in sweat and various other substances. She simply sits there on the ground, her clothes in disarray, bawling like a spoiled brat in hopes of getting her way."


translate English day11_gr_d556d2ce:


    "Thousands of emotions pass through my head, shrouded in fog. {w}Intense heat seeps into my body through the wounds that cover my skin, my nerves throbbing explosively with each blow." with sshake


translate English day11_gr_b51f25ce:


    et "The most prominent emotion of all being rapturous wonder. {w}Strong enough that I find it impossible to resist."


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_9:


    nvl clear


translate English day11_gr_1e503e6d:


    "\n \"We've been equals for a while now, you and I.\""


translate English day11_gr_41e459f8:


    "The bones that connect my head to my body bend the wrong way. {w}The world instantly goes black and just as I feel as if I'm losing my balance, I fall head over heels onto the ground." with sshake


translate English day11_gr_34bffcb4:


    "Just before I fall, I hear what sounds like thick paper crumpling in my pocket. It's probably my photos. {w}Of the two, there's only one I regret leaving behind."


translate English day11_gr_64d0870f:


    et "I lose my sight and my consciousness at roughly the same time, and the relentless pain that fills my entire body gradually fades."


translate English day11_gr_76b2fe88_10:


    nvl clear


translate English day12_gr_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day12_gr_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day12_gr_d06c1dd2:


    nar "I'm in a cramped, dark space that smells of dust. I squint against the hot, white light coming in through the small window."


translate English day12_gr_a9edb545:


    nar "The floor is cold and my way is blocked by a portcullis. Those at the temple called this insidious place the Sacrament of Penance."


translate English day12_gr_ec986074:


    nar "I hear the creak of the rusted door opening, immediately followed by the appearance of a shadowy figure against the bars."


translate English day12_gr_365edb2b:


    nar "The long silhouette, as large as the wall, grows shorter and shorter until the person at last stands in front of me."


translate English day12_gr_fe4c9940:


    gg "Well, well. So we meet again. {w}As the head of my department, I knew this was inevitable."


translate English day12_gr_3c842cf3:


    gg "I have a couple things to tell you first."


translate English day12_gr_3318a82b:


    gg "Grette is still alive, but... I can't say she's okay. {w}She has burns covering her torso and has lost the use of one eye."


translate English day12_gr_748d8334:


    gg "She says she wants to continue working regardless. Something about how she feels her life lacks meaning otherwise... She's truly something else."


translate English day12_gr_ba6739b0:


    gg "I've been in my position as bishop for quite some time now, and yet never has the mantle of responsibility felt as heavy as it does right now. {w}So let's try and lighten the mood somewhat."


translate English day12_gr_442a6776:


    gg "I know you believe I feel nothing for Grette. {w}That I simply brag about all the time I spend with her..."


translate English day12_gr_46122b9d:


    gg "I can't say you're wrong. {w}Grette is a marvelous woman. {w}Everyone describes her as ordinary, yet she has always made me believe in the power of miracles."


translate English day12_gr_c45800cf:


    gg "And I wanted to watch over that light of hers."


translate English day12_gr_30581ca5:


    gg "I'm the type of person who hates getting help from others, which is why I figured if we can be together while supporting each other in our own way without necessarily needing the other... {w}that would be ideal, or so I thought."


translate English day12_gr_683cc678:


    gg "As far as your punishment, it's not that serious. {w}Grette simply wants you to have a clean slate..."


translate English day12_gr_0628ecbc:


    gg "Under normal circumstances, I'd be punished for the violence I inflicted on you, but the situation here in the temple has gotten somewhat complicated."


translate English day12_gr_5d972e54:


    gg "We've lost everything, even Grette... {w}All we have left is our regret from our own actions."


translate English day12_gr_174486db:


    gg "Is this truly how you wanted things to end? Do you feel better now?"


translate English day12_gr_e1ec9e32:


    gg "Or are you still...?"


translate English day12_gr_996986f4:


    gg "It doesn't matter. I appreciate your hard work."


translate English day12_gr_4929f656:


    nar "And with that, he leaves the room, looking even more tired than when he arrived."


translate English day12_gr_a32b5cbd:


    nar "The cigarette he always seems to hold in his hand is not there, though his eyes seem clouded as if by the ever-present fog that follows him around."


translate English day12_gr_9ea90d05:


    gg "Don't do anything reckless..."


translate English day12_gr_51c960ec:


    nar "The bishop of the Cleanup Department silently watches him go before stepping in front of me and giving me a formal smile."


translate English day12_gr_9ad50c4a:


    hk "Hello, Brother. It's my sincerest regret that we have to meet like this."


translate English day12_gr_5b0b8a57:


    hk "But all of this happened because I was never able to properly understand you."


translate English day12_gr_f61bb26a:


    hk "It seems to me that this occurred because I was unable to lead you down the proper path, and for that, I am truly, truly sorry."


translate English day12_gr_8d7292b2:


